{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013TR84r8EAU1myQNa9dzvjH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Quarkus HTTP Configuration\n     2→quarkus.http.port=8080\n     3→quarkus.servlet.context-path=/daytrader\n     4→\n     5→# Disable SSL for simplicity (was HTTPS on 9443 in Spring)\n     6→quarkus.http.ssl.certificate.key-store-file=\n     7→quarkus.http.insecure-requests=enabled\n     8→\n     9→# Datasource Configuration (H2)\n    10→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n    11→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n    12→quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n    13→quarkus.datasource.password=\n    14→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.max-size=100\n    15→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.min-size=10\n    16→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.initial-size=10\n    17→\n    18→# Hibernate ORM - let Hibernate create tables from entities, then seed from import.sql\n    19→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    20→quarkus.hibernate-orm.sql-load-script=import.sql\n    21→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n    22→quarkus.hibernate-orm.packages=com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities\n    23→\n    24→# Artemis JMS - embedded\n    25→quarkus.artemis.url=vm://0\n    26→quarkus.artemis.username=\n    27→quarkus.artemis.password=\n    28→\n    29→# Logging\n    30→quarkus.log.level=INFO\n    31→quarkus.log.category.\"com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader\".level=DEBUG\n    32→\n    33→# DayTrader configuration properties\n    34→daytrader.runtime-mode=${DAYTRADER_RUNTIME_MODE:${RUNTIME_MODE:1}}\n    35→daytrader.order-processing-mode=${DAYTRADER_ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE:${ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE:0}}\n    36→daytrader.max-users=${DAYTRADER_MAX_USERS:${MAX_USERS:500}}\n    37→daytrader.max-quotes=${DAYTRADER_MAX_QUOTES:${MAX_QUOTES:400}}\n    38→daytrader.publish-quotes=${DAYTRADER_PUBLISH_QUOTES:${PUBLISH_QUOTES:false}}\n    39→daytrader.display-order-alerts=${DAYTRADER_DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS:${DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS:false}}\n    40→daytrader.web-interface=${DAYTRADER_WEB_INTERFACE:${WEB_INTERFACE:0}}\n    41→daytrader.list-quote-price-change-frequency=${DAYTRADER_LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY:${LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY:5}}\n    42→daytrader.prim-iterations=${DAYTRADER_PRIM_ITERATIONS:${primIterations:200}}\n    43→daytrader.market-summary-interval=${DAYTRADER_MARKET_SUMMARY_INTERVAL:${marketSummaryInterval:20}}\n    44→daytrader.long-run=${DAYTRADER_LONG_RUN:${longRun:false}}\n    45→\n    46→# Quarkus index - discover beans\n    47→quarkus.index-dependency.parsson.group-id=org.eclipse.parsson\n    48→quarkus.index-dependency.parsson.artifact-id=parsson\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"aa5aea40-2de1-4271-8eca-289b2924206c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EEFH8fxoY9aLuWSCqU9Uoq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server:\n     2→  # Liberty had httpPort=9080 and httpsPort=9443.\n     3→  # We'll run HTTPS on 9443 and add an extra HTTP connector on 9080 via a bean (this is create as a configuration in the file `src/main/java/com/ibm/daytrader/config/DualPortConfig.java`)\n     4→  port: 9443\n     5→  servlet:\n     6→    context-path: /daytrader\n     7→    session:\n     8→      timeout: 30m\n     9→  error:\n    10→    whitelabel:\n    11→      enabled: false\n    12→    path: /error\n    13→\n    14→  # This is for the keystore setting\n    15→  # <keyStore id=\"defaultKeyStore\" password=\"yourPassword\" />\n    16→  # TODO: You'll need to create the keystore file at src/main/resources/keystore.p12\n    17→  # Use `keytool` to create the keystore:\n    18→  # keytool -genkey -alias defaultKeyStore -keyalg RSA -keystore src/main/resources/keystore.p12 -storetype PKCS12 -storepass yourPassword\n    19→  ssl:\n    20→    enabled: true\n    21→    key-store: classpath:keystore.p12\n    22→    key-store-type: PKCS12\n    23→    key-store-password: yourPassword # match your Liberty <keyStore ... password=\"...\"/>\n    24→\n    25→spring:\n    26→  application:\n    27→    name: daytrader\n    28→\n    29→  sql:\n    30→    init:\n    31→      mode: always\n    32→      schema-locations: classpath:schema-h2.sql\n    33→\n    34→  jpa:\n    35→    hibernate:\n    36→      ddl-auto: none\n    37→  datasource:\n    38→    url: jdbc:h2:file:./data/tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\n    39→    username: sa\n    40→    password:\n    41→    hikari:\n    42→      maximum-pool-size: 100 # Liberty maxPoolSize=\"100\"\n    43→      minimum-idle: 100 # Liberty minPoolSize=\"100\"\n    44→      # Liberty isolationLevel=\"TRANSACTION_READ_COMMITTED\"\n    45→      transaction-isolation: TRANSACTION_READ_COMMITTED\n    46→\n    47→  # Replace wasJmsServer/Client with embedded Artemis for dev\n    48→  artemis:\n    49→    mode: embedded\n    50→    embedded:\n    51→      enabled: true\n    52→\n    53→  mvc:\n    54→    view:\n    55→      prefix: /\n    56→      suffix: .jsp\n    57→\n    58→logging:\n    59→  level:\n    60→    com.ibm.daytrader: DEBUG # Not sure what \"daytrader=fine\" means from a logging perspective, so I am setting this default.\n    61→\n    62→# --- DayTrader config (defaults).\n    63→# ENV overrides automatically in Spring Boot. To preserve your legacy env names (RUNTIME_MODE, etc.),\n    64→# we add ${ENV:...} fallbacks, so either the relaxed-name env OR your legacy env works.\n    65→# Map Liberty server.env\n    66→daytrader:\n    67→  runtime-mode: ${DAYTRADER_RUNTIME_MODE:${RUNTIME_MODE:1}}\n    68→  order-processing-mode: ${DAYTRADER_ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE:${ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE:0}}\n    69→  max-users: ${DAYTRADER_MAX_USERS:${MAX_USERS:500}}\n    70→  max-quotes: ${DAYTRADER_MAX_QUOTES:${MAX_QUOTES:400}}\n    71→  publish-quotes: ${DAYTRADER_PUBLISH_QUOTES:${PUBLISH_QUOTES:false}}\n    72→  display-order-alerts: ${DAYTRADER_DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS:${DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS:false}}\n    73→  web-interface: ${DAYTRADER_WEB_INTERFACE:${WEB_INTERFACE:0}}\n    74→  list-quote-price-change-frequency: ${DAYTRADER_LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY:${LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY:5}}\n    75→  prim-iterations: ${DAYTRADER_PRIM_ITERATIONS:${primIterations:200}}\n    76→  market-summary-interval: ${DAYTRADER_MARKET_SUMMARY_INTERVAL:${marketSummaryInterval:20}}\n    77→  long-run: ${DAYTRADER_LONG_RUN:${longRun:false}}\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"5f03e7c9-1694-4eac-96dc-b066f5bc12f0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DvE2QTjMfMHQDDtZLo2jHD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"spring-boot:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"4edaed76-fd68-4f83-adba-64a7dd69a5fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CL76w2Gi84HaH7frD2fSWS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.support.ApplicationProps;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     6→import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.EnableConfigurationProperties;\n     7→import org.springframework.boot.web.servlet.ServletComponentScan;\n     8→import org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\n     9→\n    10→@ComponentScan\n    11→@SpringBootApplication\n    12→@EnableConfigurationProperties(ApplicationProps.class)\n    13→@ServletComponentScan // Enable support for @WebServlet, @WebFilter, etc.\n    14→public class DaytraderApplication {\n    15→\n    16→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    17→        SpringApplication.run(DaytraderApplication.class, args);\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"d93bea71-a292-4505-8618-6dd9ee10cefb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KGkPP51XMnEFmFLZNEYcoF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.builder.SpringApplicationBuilder;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.web.servlet.support.SpringBootServletInitializer;\n     5→\n     6→public class ServletInitializer extends SpringBootServletInitializer {\n     7→\n     8→\t@Override\n     9→\tprotected SpringApplicationBuilder configure(SpringApplicationBuilder application) {\n    10→\t\treturn application.sources(DaytraderApplication.class);\n    11→\t}\n    12→\n    13→}\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"fd1b6e63-7ca3-4471-a89f-21953dc6d75e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PJ517RUh4ocET5Fpfnv3XN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.support;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.ConfigurationProperties;\n     4→\n     5→@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"daytrader\")\n     6→public class ApplicationProps {\n     7→    private int maxQuotes = 1000;\n     8→    private int maxUsers = 500;\n     9→\n    10→    public int getMaxQuotes() {\n    11→        return maxQuotes;\n    12→    }\n    13→\n    14→    public void setMaxQuotes(int maxQuotes) {\n    15→        this.maxQuotes = maxQuotes;\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    public int getMaxUsers() {\n    19→        return maxUsers;\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    public void setMaxUsers(int maxUsers) {\n    23→        this.maxUsers = maxUsers;\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"d9058781-15e9-4512-880d-5249ed37db6d"}
