{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01V3upyXWzXGiRnze2JaZkJX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    21→import org.springframework.web.context.support.SpringBeanAutowiringSupport;\n    22→\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    24→\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.ServletOutputStream;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    31→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    32→\n    33→/**\n    34→ *\n    35→ * PingServlet tests fundamental dynamic HTML creation functionality through\n    36→ * server side servlet processing.\n    37→ *\n    38→ */\n    39→\n    40→@Component\n    41→@WebServlet(name = \"PingServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingServlet\" })\n    42→public class PingServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    43→\n    44→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 7097023236709683760L;\n    45→    private static String initTime;\n    46→    private static int hitCount;\n    47→\n    48→    /**\n    49→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (11/6/2000\n    50→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    51→     *\n    52→     * @param res\n    53→     *             jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    54→     * @param res2\n    55→     *             jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    56→     */\n    57→    @Override\n    58→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    59→        doGet(req, res);\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    /**\n    63→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    64→     * requests.\n    65→     *\n    66→     * @param request\n    67→     *                 HttpServletRequest\n    68→     * @param responce\n    69→     *                 HttpServletResponce\n    70→     **/\n    71→    @Override\n    72→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    73→        try {\n    74→            res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    75→\n    76→            // The following 2 lines are the difference between PingServlet and\n    77→            // PingServletWriter\n    78→            // the latter uses a PrintWriter for output versus a binary output\n    79→            // stream.\n    80→            ServletOutputStream out = res.getOutputStream();\n    81→            // java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    82→            hitCount++;\n    83→            out.println(\"<html><head><title>Ping Servlet</title></head>\"\n    84→                    + \"<body><HR><BR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping Servlet<BR></FONT><FONT size=\\\"+1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \"\n    85→                    + initTime\n    86→                    + \"<BR><BR></FONT>  <B>Hit Count: \" + hitCount + \"</B></body></html>\");\n    87→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    88→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet.doGet(...): general exception caught\");\n    89→            res.sendError(500, e.toString());\n    90→\n    91→        }\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    /**\n    95→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n    96→     *\n    97→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n    98→     **/\n    99→    @Override\n   100→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   101→        return \"Basic dynamic HTML generation through a servlet\";\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    /**\n   105→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   106→     *\n   107→     * @param config\n   108→     *               ServletConfig:\n   109→     **/\n   110→    @Override\n   111→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   112→        super.init(config);\n   113→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   114→        hitCount = 0;\n   115→        SpringBeanAutowiringSupport.processInjectionBasedOnServletContext(this, config.getServletContext());\n   116→\n   117→    }\n   118→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MYxW4uTPhXMTMU8Sq7ArXi","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c669ac58-266c-4844-a827-21cdb217bebd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C552SihyegrkVNMFZ1VTYA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims.cdi;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.context.support.SpringBeanAutowiringSupport;\n    24→\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    31→\n    32→@Component\n    33→@WebServlet(\"/servlet/PingServletCDI\")\n    34→public class PingServletCDI extends HttpServlet {\n    35→\n    36→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -1803544618879689949L;\n    37→  private static String initTime;\n    38→\n    39→  @Autowired\n    40→  PingCDIBean cdiBean;\n    41→\n    42→  @Autowired\n    43→  PingEJBIFace ejb;\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws IOException {\n    47→\n    48→    PrintWriter pw = response.getWriter();\n    49→    pw.write(\"<html><head><title>Ping Servlet CDI</title></head>\"\n    50→        + \"<body><HR><BR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping Servlet CDI<BR></FONT><FONT size=\\\"+1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \"\n    51→        + initTime\n    52→        + \"<BR><BR></FONT>\");\n    53→\n    54→    pw.write(\"<B>hitCount: \" + cdiBean.hello() + \"</B><BR>\");\n    55→    pw.write(\"<B>hitCount: \" + ejb.getMsg() + \"</B><BR>\");\n    56→\n    57→    pw.flush();\n    58→    pw.close();\n    59→\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  /**\n    63→   * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n    64→   * \n    65→   * @param config\n    66→   *               ServletConfig:\n    67→   **/\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    70→    super.init(config);\n    71→    SpringBeanAutowiringSupport.processInjectionBasedOnServletContext(this, config.getServletContext());\n    72→    initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n    73→\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MYxW4uTPhXMTMU8Sq7ArXi","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"75632d05-e858-44d3-8552-7f36dfefee64"}
