{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017PxBwsyx8S5FA7WyYUzJse","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→-- DayTrader schema for H2\n     2→-- Intentionally idempotent (safe to run on every startup).\n     3→\n     4→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS ACCOUNTPROFILEEJB (\n     5→  ADDRESS VARCHAR(250),\n     6→  PASSWD VARCHAR(250),\n     7→  USERID VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,\n     8→  EMAIL VARCHAR(250),\n     9→  CREDITCARD VARCHAR(250),\n    10→  FULLNAME VARCHAR(250),\n    11→  CONSTRAINT PK_ACCOUNTPROFILEEJB PRIMARY KEY (USERID)\n    12→);\n    13→\n    14→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS KEYGENEJB (\n    15→  KEYVAL INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    16→  KEYNAME VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,\n    17→  CONSTRAINT PK_KEYGENEJB PRIMARY KEY (KEYNAME)\n    18→);\n    19→\n    20→MERGE INTO KEYGENEJB (KEYNAME, KEYVAL) KEY (KEYNAME) VALUES ('account', 0);\n    21→MERGE INTO KEYGENEJB (KEYNAME, KEYVAL) KEY (KEYNAME) VALUES ('holding', 0);\n    22→MERGE INTO KEYGENEJB (KEYNAME, KEYVAL) KEY (KEYNAME) VALUES ('order', 0);\n    23→\n    24→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS ACCOUNTEJB (\n    25→  CREATIONDATE TIMESTAMP,\n    26→  OPENBALANCE DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    27→  LOGOUTCOUNT INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    28→  BALANCE DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    29→  ACCOUNTID INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    30→  LASTLOGIN TIMESTAMP,\n    31→  LOGINCOUNT INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    32→  PROFILE_USERID VARCHAR(250),\n    33→  CONSTRAINT PK_ACCOUNTEJB PRIMARY KEY (ACCOUNTID)\n    34→);\n    35→\n    36→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS QUOTEEJB (\n    37→  LOW DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    38→  OPEN1 DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    39→  VOLUME DOUBLE NOT NULL,\n    40→  PRICE DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    41→  HIGH DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    42→  COMPANYNAME VARCHAR(250),\n    43→  SYMBOL VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,\n    44→  CHANGE1 DOUBLE NOT NULL,\n    45→  CONSTRAINT PK_QUOTEEJB PRIMARY KEY (SYMBOL)\n    46→);\n    47→\n    48→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS HOLDINGEJB (\n    49→  PURCHASEPRICE DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    50→  HOLDINGID INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    51→  QUANTITY DOUBLE NOT NULL,\n    52→  PURCHASEDATE TIMESTAMP,\n    53→  ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID INTEGER,\n    54→  QUOTE_SYMBOL VARCHAR(250),\n    55→  CONSTRAINT PK_HOLDINGEJB PRIMARY KEY (HOLDINGID)\n    56→);\n    57→\n    58→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS ORDEREJB (\n    59→  ORDERFEE DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    60→  COMPLETIONDATE TIMESTAMP,\n    61→  ORDERTYPE VARCHAR(250),\n    62→  ORDERSTATUS VARCHAR(250),\n    63→  PRICE DECIMAL(14, 2),\n    64→  QUANTITY DOUBLE NOT NULL,\n    65→  OPENDATE TIMESTAMP,\n    66→  ORDERID INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    67→  ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID INTEGER,\n    68→  QUOTE_SYMBOL VARCHAR(250),\n    69→  HOLDING_HOLDINGID INTEGER,\n    70→  CONSTRAINT PK_ORDEREJB PRIMARY KEY (ORDERID)\n    71→);\n    72→\n    73→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS ACCOUNT_USERID ON ACCOUNTEJB(PROFILE_USERID);\n    74→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS HOLDING_ACCOUNTID ON HOLDINGEJB(ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID);\n    75→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS ORDER_ACCOUNTID ON ORDEREJB(ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID);\n    76→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS ORDER_HOLDINGID ON ORDEREJB(HOLDING_HOLDINGID);\n    77→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS CLOSED_ORDERS ON ORDEREJB(ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID, ORDERSTATUS);\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"8308ef97-1485-4a73-8ec0-8f791a08ab43"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ki1jeud4PCpaXanKrf83Vm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→-- DayTrader initial seed data for Quarkus/Hibernate\n     2→-- The keygenejb table is used by KeySequenceDirect for ID generation\n     3→-- This table is NOT a JPA entity, so we need to create it manually\n     4→\n     5→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS KEYGENEJB (\n     6→  KEYVAL INTEGER NOT NULL,\n     7→  KEYNAME VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,\n     8→  CONSTRAINT PK_KEYGENEJB PRIMARY KEY (KEYNAME)\n     9→);\n    10→\n    11→INSERT INTO KEYGENEJB (KEYNAME, KEYVAL) VALUES ('account', 0);\n    12→INSERT INTO KEYGENEJB (KEYNAME, KEYVAL) VALUES ('holding', 0);\n    13→INSERT INTO KEYGENEJB (KEYNAME, KEYVAL) VALUES ('order', 0);\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"99b3d558-bcb4-4882-a34a-3c33939d0561"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PnuWwQtqtDg7oKGhtbhqLn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    23→\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.NamedNativeQueries;\n    28→import jakarta.persistence.NamedNativeQuery;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    32→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    33→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    34→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    35→\n    36→@Entity(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    37→@Table(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    38→@NamedQueries({\n    39→        @NamedQuery(name = \"quoteejb.allQuotes\", query = \"SELECT q FROM quoteejb q\") })\n    40→@NamedNativeQueries({\n    41→        @NamedNativeQuery(name = \"quoteejb.quoteForUpdate\", query = \"select * from quoteejb q where q.symbol=? for update\", resultClass = com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean.class) })\n    42→public class QuoteDataBean implements Serializable {\n    43→\n    44→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    45→\n    46→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1847932261895838791L;\n    47→\n    48→    @Id\n    49→    @NotNull\n    50→    @Column(name = \"SYMBOL\", nullable = false)\n    51→    private String symbol; /* symbol */\n    52→\n    53→    @Column(name = \"COMPANYNAME\")\n    54→    @NotBlank\n    55→    private String companyName; /* companyName */\n    56→\n    57→    @NotNull\n    58→    @Column(name = \"VOLUME\", nullable = false)\n    59→    private double volume; /* volume */\n    60→\n    61→    @Column(name = \"PRICE\")\n    62→    @Positive\n    63→    private BigDecimal price; /* price */\n    64→\n    65→    @Column(name = \"OPEN1\")\n    66→    @Positive\n    67→    private BigDecimal open1; /* open1 price */\n    68→\n    69→    @Column(name = \"LOW\")\n    70→    @Positive\n    71→    private BigDecimal low; /* low price */\n    72→\n    73→    @Column(name = \"HIGH\")\n    74→    @Positive\n    75→    private BigDecimal high; /* high price */\n    76→\n    77→    @NotNull\n    78→    @Column(name = \"CHANGE1\", nullable = false)\n    79→    private double change1; /* price change */\n    80→\n    81→    /* Accessor methods for relationship fields are not kept in the DataBean */\n    82→\n    83→    public QuoteDataBean() {\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol, String companyName, double volume, BigDecimal price, BigDecimal open,\n    87→            BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high, double change) {\n    88→        setSymbol(symbol);\n    89→        setCompanyName(companyName);\n    90→        setVolume(volume);\n    91→        setPrice(price);\n    92→        setOpen(open);\n    93→        setLow(low);\n    94→        setHigh(high);\n    95→        setChange(change);\n    96→    }\n    97→\n    98→    public static QuoteDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    99→        return new QuoteDataBean(TradeConfig.rndSymbol(), // symbol\n   100→                TradeConfig.rndSymbol() + \" Incorporated\", // Company Name\n   101→                TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000), // volume\n   102→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // price\n   103→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // open1\n   104→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // low\n   105→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // high\n   106→                TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000) // volume\n   107→        );\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    // Create a \"zero\" value quoteDataBean for the given symbol\n   111→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol) {\n   112→        setSymbol(symbol);\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    @Override\n   116→    public String toString() {\n   117→        return \"\\n\\tQuote Data for: \" + getSymbol() + \"\\n\\t\\t companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume: \"\n   118→                + getVolume() + \"\\n\\t\\t       price: \"\n   119→                + getPrice() + \"\\n\\t\\t        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"\\n\\t\\t         low: \" + getLow()\n   120→                + \"\\n\\t\\t        high: \" + getHigh()\n   121→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      change1: \" + getChange();\n   122→    }\n   123→\n   124→    public String toHTML() {\n   125→        return \"<BR>Quote Data for: \" + getSymbol() + \"<LI> companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"</LI>\"\n   126→                + \"<LI>      volume: \" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\"\n   127→                + \"<LI>       price: \" + getPrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"</LI>\"\n   128→                + \"<LI>         low: \" + getLow() + \"</LI>\"\n   129→                + \"<LI>        high: \" + getHigh() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      change1: \" + getChange() + \"</LI>\";\n   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    public void print() {\n   133→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    public String getSymbol() {\n   137→        return symbol;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n   141→        this.symbol = symbol;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public String getCompanyName() {\n   145→        return companyName;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public void setCompanyName(String companyName) {\n   149→        this.companyName = companyName;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n   153→        return price;\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   157→        this.price = price;\n   158→    }\n   159→\n   160→    public BigDecimal getOpen() {\n   161→        return open1;\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    public void setOpen(BigDecimal open) {\n   165→        this.open1 = open;\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    public BigDecimal getLow() {\n   169→        return low;\n   170→    }\n   171→\n   172→    public void setLow(BigDecimal low) {\n   173→        this.low = low;\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    public BigDecimal getHigh() {\n   177→        return high;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    public void setHigh(BigDecimal high) {\n   181→        this.high = high;\n   182→    }\n   183→\n   184→    public double getChange() {\n   185→        return change1;\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    public void setChange(double change) {\n   189→        this.change1 = change;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    public double getVolume() {\n   193→        return volume;\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   197→        this.volume = volume;\n   198→    }\n   199→\n   200→    @Override\n   201→    public int hashCode() {\n   202→        int hash = 0;\n   203→        hash += (this.symbol != null ? this.symbol.hashCode() : 0);\n   204→        return hash;\n   205→    }\n   206→\n   207→    @Override\n   208→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   209→\n   210→        if (!(object instanceof QuoteDataBean)) {\n   211→            return false;\n   212→        }\n   213→        QuoteDataBean other = (QuoteDataBean) object;\n   214→        if (this.symbol != other.symbol && (this.symbol == null || !this.symbol.equals(other.symbol))) {\n   215→            return false;\n   216→        }\n   217→        return true;\n   218→    }\n   219→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"e57778d7-6b21-4789-b1f1-cee78867fb78"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KWZrayDF25foQPVcbBtvkL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n     5→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→import java.util.Date;\n     8→\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    13→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n    14→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    15→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    16→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    17→import jakarta.persistence.OneToOne;\n    18→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    19→import jakarta.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    20→import jakarta.persistence.Temporal;\n    21→import jakarta.persistence.TemporalType;\n    22→import jakarta.persistence.Transient;\n    23→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    24→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    25→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PositiveOrZero;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    29→\n    30→@Entity(name = \"accountejb\")\n    31→@Table(name = \"accountejb\")\n    32→public class AccountDataBean implements Serializable {\n    33→\n    34→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 8437841265136840545L;\n    35→\n    36→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    37→    @TableGenerator(name = \"accountIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"account\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    38→    @Id\n    39→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"accountIdGen\")\n    40→    @Column(name = \"ACCOUNTID\", nullable = false)\n    41→    private Integer accountID; /* accountID */\n    42→\n    43→    @NotNull\n    44→    @PositiveOrZero\n    45→    @Column(name = \"LOGINCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    46→    private int loginCount; /* loginCount */\n    47→\n    48→    @NotNull\n    49→    @PositiveOrZero\n    50→    @Column(name = \"LOGOUTCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    51→    private int logoutCount; /* logoutCount */\n    52→\n    53→    @Column(name = \"LASTLOGIN\")\n    54→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    55→    @PastOrPresent\n    56→    private Date lastLogin; /* lastLogin Date */\n    57→\n    58→    @Column(name = \"CREATIONDATE\")\n    59→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    60→    @PastOrPresent\n    61→    private Date creationDate; /* creationDate */\n    62→\n    63→    @Column(name = \"BALANCE\")\n    64→    private BigDecimal balance; /* balance */\n    65→\n    66→    @Column(name = \"OPENBALANCE\")\n    67→    private BigDecimal openBalance; /* open balance */\n    68→\n    69→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    70→    private Collection<OrderDataBean> orders;\n    71→\n    72→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    73→    private Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings;\n    74→\n    75→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    76→    @JoinColumn(name = \"PROFILE_USERID\")\n    77→    private AccountProfileDataBean profile;\n    78→\n    79→    /*\n    80→     * Accessor methods for relationship fields are only included for the\n    81→     * AccountProfile profileID\n    82→     */\n    83→    @Transient\n    84→    private String profileID;\n    85→\n    86→    public AccountDataBean() {\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    public AccountDataBean(Integer accountID, int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate,\n    90→            BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance,\n    91→            String profileID) {\n    92→        setAccountID(accountID);\n    93→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n    94→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n    95→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n    96→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n    97→        setBalance(balance);\n    98→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n    99→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    public AccountDataBean(int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance,\n   103→            BigDecimal openBalance, String profileID) {\n   104→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   105→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   106→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   107→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   108→        setBalance(balance);\n   109→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   110→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    public static AccountDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   114→        return new AccountDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), // accountID\n   115→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // loginCount\n   116→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // logoutCount\n   117→                new java.util.Date(), // lastLogin\n   118→                new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), // creationDate\n   119→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // balance\n   120→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // openBalance\n   121→                TradeConfig.rndUserID() // profileID\n   122→        );\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    @Override\n   126→    public String toString() {\n   127→        return \"\\n\\tAccount Data for account: \" + getAccountID() + \"\\n\\t\\t   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount()\n   128→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  logoutCount:\" + getLogoutCount()\n   129→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"\\n\\t\\t creationDate:\" + getCreationDate()\n   130→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      balance:\" + getBalance()\n   131→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"\\n\\t\\t    profileID:\" + getProfileID();\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    public String toHTML() {\n   135→        return \"<BR>Account Data for account: <B>\" + getAccountID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount()\n   136→                + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  logoutCount:\"\n   137→                + getLogoutCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> creationDate:\"\n   138→                + getCreationDate() + \"</LI>\"\n   139→                + \"<LI>      balance:\" + getBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"</LI>\"\n   140→                + \"<LI>    profileID:\" + getProfileID()\n   141→                + \"</LI>\";\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public void print() {\n   145→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public Integer getAccountID() {\n   149→        return accountID;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public void setAccountID(Integer accountID) {\n   153→        this.accountID = accountID;\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    public int getLoginCount() {\n   157→        return loginCount;\n   158→    }\n   159→\n   160→    public void setLoginCount(int loginCount) {\n   161→        this.loginCount = loginCount;\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    public int getLogoutCount() {\n   165→        return logoutCount;\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    public void setLogoutCount(int logoutCount) {\n   169→        this.logoutCount = logoutCount;\n   170→    }\n   171→\n   172→    public Date getLastLogin() {\n   173→        return lastLogin;\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    public void setLastLogin(Date lastLogin) {\n   177→        this.lastLogin = lastLogin;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    public Date getCreationDate() {\n   181→        return creationDate;\n   182→    }\n   183→\n   184→    public void setCreationDate(Date creationDate) {\n   185→        this.creationDate = creationDate;\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    public BigDecimal getBalance() {\n   189→        return balance;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    public void setBalance(BigDecimal balance) {\n   193→        this.balance = balance;\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    public BigDecimal getOpenBalance() {\n   197→        return openBalance;\n   198→    }\n   199→\n   200→    public void setOpenBalance(BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   201→        this.openBalance = openBalance;\n   202→    }\n   203→\n   204→    public String getProfileID() {\n   205→        return profileID;\n   206→    }\n   207→\n   208→    public void setProfileID(String profileID) {\n   209→        this.profileID = profileID;\n   210→    }\n   211→\n   212→    /*\n   213→     * Disabled for D185273 public String getUserID() { return getProfileID(); }\n   214→     */\n   215→\n   216→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders() {\n   217→        return orders;\n   218→    }\n   219→\n   220→    public void setOrders(Collection<OrderDataBean> orders) {\n   221→        this.orders = orders;\n   222→    }\n   223→\n   224→    public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings() {\n   225→        return holdings;\n   226→    }\n   227→\n   228→    public void setHoldings(Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings) {\n   229→        this.holdings = holdings;\n   230→    }\n   231→\n   232→    public AccountProfileDataBean getProfile() {\n   233→        return profile;\n   234→    }\n   235→\n   236→    public void setProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profile) {\n   237→        this.profile = profile;\n   238→    }\n   239→\n   240→    public void login(String password) {\n   241→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = getProfile();\n   242→        if ((profile == null) || (profile.getPassword().equals(password) == false)) {\n   243→            String error = \"AccountBean:Login failure for account: \" + getAccountID()\n   244→                    + ((profile == null) ? \"null AccountProfile\"\n   245→                            : \"\\n\\tIncorrect password-->\" + profile.getUserID() + \":\" + profile.getPassword());\n   246→            throw new IllegalStateException(error);\n   247→        }\n   248→\n   249→        setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   250→        setLoginCount(getLoginCount() + 1);\n   251→    }\n   252→\n   253→    public void logout() {\n   254→        setLogoutCount(getLogoutCount() + 1);\n   255→    }\n   256→\n   257→    @Override\n   258→    public int hashCode() {\n   259→        int hash = 0;\n   260→        hash += (this.accountID != null ? this.accountID.hashCode() : 0);\n   261→        return hash;\n   262→    }\n   263→\n   264→    @Override\n   265→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   266→\n   267→        if (!(object instanceof AccountDataBean)) {\n   268→            return false;\n   269→        }\n   270→        AccountDataBean other = (AccountDataBean) object;\n   271→\n   272→        if (this.accountID != other.accountID && (this.accountID == null || !this.accountID.equals(other.accountID))) {\n   273→            return false;\n   274→        }\n   275→\n   276→        return true;\n   277→    }\n   278→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"fc3b7430-e39b-4dc7-aaae-ae193b78d8a1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WSJzZQg6NDUdUkDLusCzfQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.Random;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * TradeConfig is a JavaBean holding all configuration and runtime parameters\n    24→ * for the Trade application TradeConfig sets runtime parameters such as the\n    25→ * RunTimeMode (EJB, JDBC, EJB_ALT)\n    26→ *\n    27→ */\n    28→\n    29→public class TradeConfig {\n    30→\n    31→  /* Trade Runtime Configuration Parameters */\n    32→\n    33→  /* Trade Runtime Mode parameters */\n    34→  private static String[] runTimeModeNames = { \"Full EJB3\", \"Direct (JDBC)\", \"Session to Direct\" };\n    35→  public static final int EJB3 = 0;\n    36→  public static final int DIRECT = 1;\n    37→  public static final int SESSION_TO_DIRECT = 2;\n    38→  private static int runTimeMode = EJB3;\n    39→\n    40→  private static String[] orderProcessingModeNames = { \"Sync\", \"Async\", \"Async_2-Phase\" };\n    41→  public static final int SYNCH = 0;\n    42→  public static final int ASYNCH = 1;\n    43→  public static final int ASYNCH_2PHASE = 2;\n    44→  private static int orderProcessingMode = SYNCH;\n    45→\n    46→  private static String[] accessModeNames = { \"Standard\", \"WebServices\" };\n    47→  public static final int STANDARD = 0;\n    48→  private static int accessMode = STANDARD;\n    49→\n    50→  /* Trade Web Interface parameters */\n    51→  private static String[] webInterfaceNames = { \"JSP\", \"JSP-Images\", \"JSP-Images-Http2\" };\n    52→  public static final int JSP = 0;\n    53→  public static final int JSP_Images = 1;\n    54→  public static final int JSP_Images_HTTP2 = 2;\n    55→  private static int webInterface = JSP;\n    56→\n    57→  /* Trade Database Scaling parameters */\n    58→  private static int MAX_USERS = 15000;\n    59→  private static int MAX_QUOTES = 10000;\n    60→\n    61→  /* Trade XA Datasource specific parameters */\n    62→  public static boolean JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation = false;\n    63→\n    64→  /* Trade Config Miscellaneous itmes */\n    65→  public static String DATASOURCE = \"java:comp/env/jdbc/TradeDataSource\";\n    66→  public static int KEYBLOCKSIZE = 1000;\n    67→  public static int QUOTES_PER_PAGE = 10;\n    68→  public static boolean RND_USER = true;\n    69→  // public static int RND_SEED = 0;\n    70→  private static int MAX_HOLDINGS = 10;\n    71→  private static int count = 0;\n    72→  private static Object userID_count_semaphore = new Object();\n    73→  private static int userID_count = 0;\n    74→  private static String hostName = null;\n    75→  private static Random r0 = new Random(System.currentTimeMillis());\n    76→  // private static Random r1 = new Random(RND_SEED);\n    77→  private static Random randomNumberGenerator = r0;\n    78→  public static final String newUserPrefix = \"ru:\";\n    79→  public static final int verifyPercent = 5;\n    80→  private static boolean updateQuotePrices = true;\n    81→  private static int primIterations = 1;\n    82→  private static boolean longRun = true;\n    83→  private static boolean publishQuotePriceChange = true;\n    84→  private static int listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = 100;\n    85→  private static boolean displayOrderAlerts = true;\n    86→\n    87→  /**\n    88→   * -1 means every operation 0 means never perform a market summary > 0 means\n    89→   * number of seconds between summaries. These will be synchronized so only\n    90→   * one transaction in this period will create a summary and will cache its\n    91→   * results.\n    92→   */\n    93→  private static int marketSummaryInterval = 20;\n    94→\n    95→  /*\n    96→   * Penny stocks is a problem where the random price change factor gets a\n    97→   * stock down to $.01. In this case trade jumpstarts the price back to $6.00\n    98→   * to keep the math interesting.\n    99→   */\n   100→  public static BigDecimal PENNY_STOCK_PRICE;\n   101→  public static BigDecimal PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER;\n   102→  static {\n   103→    PENNY_STOCK_PRICE = new BigDecimal(0.01);\n   104→    PENNY_STOCK_PRICE = PENNY_STOCK_PRICE.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   105→    PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER = new BigDecimal(600.0);\n   106→    PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   107→  }\n   108→\n   109→  /*\n   110→   * CJB (DAYTRADER-25) - Also need to impose a ceiling on the quote price to\n   111→   * ensure prevent account and holding balances from exceeding the databases\n   112→   * decimal precision. At some point, this maximum value can be used to\n   113→   * trigger a stock split.\n   114→   */\n   115→\n   116→  public static BigDecimal MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE;\n   117→  public static BigDecimal MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER;\n   118→  static {\n   119→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE = new BigDecimal(400);\n   120→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   121→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER = new BigDecimal(0.5);\n   122→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  /*\n   126→   * Trade Scenario actions mixes. Each of the array rows represents a\n   127→   * specific Trade Scenario Mix. The columns give the percentages for each\n   128→   * action in the column header. Note: \"login\" is always 0. logout represents\n   129→   * both login and logout (because each logout operation will cause a new\n   130→   * login when the user context attempts the next action.\n   131→   */\n   132→  /* Trade Scenario Workload parameters */\n   133→  public static final int HOME_OP = 0;\n   134→  public static final int QUOTE_OP = 1;\n   135→  public static final int LOGIN_OP = 2;\n   136→  public static final int LOGOUT_OP = 3;\n   137→  public static final int REGISTER_OP = 4;\n   138→  public static final int ACCOUNT_OP = 5;\n   139→  public static final int PORTFOLIO_OP = 6;\n   140→  public static final int BUY_OP = 7;\n   141→  public static final int SELL_OP = 8;\n   142→  public static final int UPDATEACCOUNT_OP = 9;\n   143→\n   144→  private static int[][] scenarioMixes = {\n   145→      // h q l o r a p b s u\n   146→      { 20, 40, 0, 4, 2, 10, 12, 4, 4, 4 }, // STANDARD\n   147→      { 20, 40, 0, 4, 2, 7, 7, 7, 7, 6 }, // High Volume\n   148→  };\n   149→  private static char[] actions = { 'h', 'q', 'l', 'o', 'r', 'a', 'p', 'b', 's', 'u' };\n   150→  private static int sellDeficit = 0;\n   151→  // Tracks the number of buys over sell when a users portfolio is empty\n   152→  // Used to maintain the correct ratio of buys/sells\n   153→\n   154→  /* JSP pages for all Trade Actions */\n   155→\n   156→  public static final int WELCOME_PAGE = 0;\n   157→  public static final int REGISTER_PAGE = 1;\n   158→  public static final int PORTFOLIO_PAGE = 2;\n   159→  public static final int QUOTE_PAGE = 3;\n   160→  public static final int HOME_PAGE = 4;\n   161→  public static final int ACCOUNT_PAGE = 5;\n   162→  public static final int ORDER_PAGE = 6;\n   163→  public static final int CONFIG_PAGE = 7;\n   164→  public static final int STATS_PAGE = 8;\n   165→  public static final int MARKET_SUMMARY_PAGE = 9;\n   166→\n   167→  // FUTURE Add XML/XSL View\n   168→  public static String[][] webUI = {\n   169→      { \"/welcome.jsp\", \"/register.jsp\", \"/portfolio.jsp\", \"/quote.jsp\", \"/tradehome.jsp\", \"/account.jsp\", \"/order.jsp\",\n   170→          \"/config.jsp\", \"/runStats.jsp\",\n   171→          \"/marketSummary.jsp\" },\n   172→      // JSP Interface\n   173→      { \"/welcomeImg.jsp\", \"/registerImg.jsp\", \"/portfolioImg.jsp\", \"/quoteImg.jsp\", \"/tradehomeImg.jsp\",\n   174→          \"/accountImg.jsp\", \"/orderImg.jsp\",\n   175→          \"/config.jsp\", \"/runStats.jsp\", \"/marketSummary.jsp\" },\n   176→      // JSP Interface\n   177→      { \"/welcomeImg.jsp\", \"/registerImg.jsp\", \"/portfolioImg.jsp\", \"/quoteImg.jsp\", \"/tradehomeImg.jsp\",\n   178→          \"/accountImg.jsp\", \"/orderImg.jsp\",\n   179→          \"/config.jsp\", \"/runStats.jsp\", \"/marketSummary.jsp\" },\n   180→  };\n   181→\n   182→  /**\n   183→   * Return the hostname for this system Creation date: (2/16/2000 9:02:25 PM)\n   184→   */\n   185→\n   186→  private static String getHostname() {\n   187→    try {\n   188→      if (hostName == null) {\n   189→        hostName = java.net.InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName();\n   190→        // Strip of fully qualifed domain if necessary\n   191→        try {\n   192→          hostName = hostName.substring(0, hostName.indexOf('.'));\n   193→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   194→        }\n   195→      }\n   196→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   197→      Log.error(\"Exception getting local host name using 'localhost' - \", e);\n   198→      hostName = \"localhost\";\n   199→    }\n   200→    return hostName;\n   201→  }\n   202→\n   203→  /**\n   204→   * Return a Trade UI Web page based on the current configuration This may\n   205→   * return a JSP page or a Servlet page Creation date: (3/14/2000 9:08:34 PM)\n   206→   */\n   207→\n   208→  public static String getPage(int pageNumber) {\n   209→    return webUI[webInterface][pageNumber];\n   210→  }\n   211→\n   212→  /**\n   213→   * Return the list of run time mode names Creation date: (3/8/2000 5:58:34\n   214→   * PM)\n   215→   *\n   216→   * @return java.lang.String[]\n   217→   */\n   218→  public static java.lang.String[] getRunTimeModeNames() {\n   219→    return runTimeModeNames;\n   220→  }\n   221→\n   222→  private static int scenarioCount = 0;\n   223→\n   224→  /**\n   225→   * Return a Trade Scenario Operation based on the setting of the current mix\n   226→   * (TradeScenarioMix) Creation date: (2/10/2000 9:08:34 PM)\n   227→   */\n   228→\n   229→  public static char getScenarioAction(boolean newUser) {\n   230→    int r = rndInt(100); // 0 to 99 = 100\n   231→    int i = 0;\n   232→    int sum = scenarioMixes[0][i];\n   233→    while (sum <= r) {\n   234→      i++;\n   235→      sum += scenarioMixes[0][i];\n   236→    }\n   237→\n   238→    incrementScenarioCount();\n   239→\n   240→    /*\n   241→     * In TradeScenarioServlet, if a sell action is selected, but the users\n   242→     * portfolio is empty, a buy is executed instead and sellDefecit is\n   243→     * incremented. This allows the number of buy/sell operations to stay in\n   244→     * sync w/ the given Trade mix.\n   245→     */\n   246→\n   247→    if ((!newUser) && (actions[i] == 'b')) {\n   248→      synchronized (TradeConfig.class) {\n   249→        if (sellDeficit > 0) {\n   250→          sellDeficit--;\n   251→          return 's';\n   252→          // Special case for TradeScenarioServlet to note this is a\n   253→          // buy switched to a sell to fix sellDeficit\n   254→        }\n   255→      }\n   256→    }\n   257→\n   258→    return actions[i];\n   259→  }\n   260→\n   261→  public static String getUserID() {\n   262→    String userID;\n   263→    if (RND_USER) {\n   264→      userID = rndUserID();\n   265→    } else {\n   266→      userID = nextUserID();\n   267→    }\n   268→    return userID;\n   269→  }\n   270→\n   271→  private static final BigDecimal orderFee = new BigDecimal(\"24.95\");\n   272→  private static final BigDecimal cashFee = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\");\n   273→\n   274→  public static BigDecimal getOrderFee(String orderType) {\n   275→    if ((orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"BUY\") == 0) || (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"SELL\") == 0)) {\n   276→      return orderFee;\n   277→    }\n   278→\n   279→    return cashFee;\n   280→\n   281→  }\n   282→\n   283→  /**\n   284→   * Increment the sell deficit counter Creation date: (6/21/2000 11:33:45 AM)\n   285→   */\n   286→  public static synchronized void incrementSellDeficit() {\n   287→    sellDeficit++;\n   288→  }\n   289→\n   290→  public static String nextUserID() {\n   291→    String userID;\n   292→    synchronized (userID_count_semaphore) {\n   293→      userID = \"uid:\" + userID_count;\n   294→      userID_count++;\n   295→      if (userID_count % MAX_USERS == 0) {\n   296→        userID_count = 0;\n   297→      }\n   298→    }\n   299→    return userID;\n   300→  }\n   301→\n   302→  public static double random() {\n   303→    return randomNumberGenerator.nextDouble();\n   304→  }\n   305→\n   306→  public static String rndAddress() {\n   307→    return rndInt(1000) + \" Oak St.\";\n   308→  }\n   309→\n   310→  public static String rndBalance() {\n   311→    // Give all new users a cool mill in which to trade\n   312→    return \"1000000\";\n   313→  }\n   314→\n   315→  public static String rndCreditCard() {\n   316→    return rndInt(100) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000);\n   317→  }\n   318→\n   319→  public static String rndEmail(String userID) {\n   320→    return userID.replace(\":\", \"\") + \"@\" + rndInt(100) + \".com\";\n   321→  }\n   322→\n   323→  public static String rndFullName() {\n   324→    return \"first:\" + rndInt(1000) + \" last:\" + rndInt(5000);\n   325→  }\n   326→\n   327→  public static int rndInt(int i) {\n   328→    return (new Float(random() * i)).intValue();\n   329→  }\n   330→\n   331→  public static float rndFloat(int i) {\n   332→    return (new Float(random() * i)).floatValue();\n   333→  }\n   334→\n   335→  public static BigDecimal rndBigDecimal(float f) {\n   336→    return (new BigDecimal(random() * f)).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   337→  }\n   338→\n   339→  public static boolean rndBoolean() {\n   340→    return randomNumberGenerator.nextBoolean();\n   341→  }\n   342→\n   343→  /**\n   344→   * Returns a new Trade user Creation date: (2/16/2000 8:50:35 PM)\n   345→   */\n   346→  public static synchronized String rndNewUserID() {\n   347→\n   348→    return newUserPrefix + getHostname() + System.currentTimeMillis() + count++;\n   349→  }\n   350→\n   351→  public static float rndPrice() {\n   352→    return ((new Integer(rndInt(200))).floatValue()) + 1.0f;\n   353→  }\n   354→\n   355→  private static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(1.0);\n   356→\n   357→  public static BigDecimal getRandomPriceChangeFactor() {\n   358→    // CJB (DAYTRADER-25) - Vary change factor between 1.1 and 0.9\n   359→    double percentGain = rndFloat(1) * 0.1;\n   360→    if (random() < .5) {\n   361→      percentGain *= -1;\n   362→    }\n   363→    percentGain += 1;\n   364→\n   365→    // change factor is between +/- 20%\n   366→    BigDecimal percentGainBD = (new BigDecimal(percentGain)).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   367→    if (percentGainBD.doubleValue() <= 0.0) {\n   368→      percentGainBD = ONE;\n   369→    }\n   370→\n   371→    return percentGainBD;\n   372→  }\n   373→\n   374→  public static float rndQuantity() {\n   375→    return ((new Integer(rndInt(200))).floatValue()) + 1.0f;\n   376→  }\n   377→\n   378→  public static String rndSymbol() {\n   379→    return \"s:\" + rndInt(MAX_QUOTES - 1);\n   380→  }\n   381→\n   382→  public static String rndSymbols() {\n   383→\n   384→    String symbols = \"\";\n   385→    int num_symbols = rndInt(QUOTES_PER_PAGE);\n   386→\n   387→    for (int i = 0; i <= num_symbols; i++) {\n   388→      symbols += \"s:\" + rndInt(MAX_QUOTES - 1);\n   389→      if (i < num_symbols) {\n   390→        symbols += \",\";\n   391→      }\n   392→    }\n   393→    return symbols;\n   394→  }\n   395→\n   396→  public static String rndUserID() {\n   397→    String nextUser = getNextUserIDFromDeck();\n   398→\n   399→    Log.trace(\"TradeConfig:rndUserID -- new trader = \" + nextUser);\n   400→\n   401→    return nextUser;\n   402→  }\n   403→\n   404→  private static synchronized String getNextUserIDFromDeck() {\n   405→    int numUsers = getMAX_USERS();\n   406→    if (deck == null) {\n   407→      deck = new ArrayList<Integer>(numUsers);\n   408→      for (int i = 0; i < numUsers; i++) {\n   409→        deck.add(i, new Integer(i));\n   410→      }\n   411→      java.util.Collections.shuffle(deck, r0);\n   412→    }\n   413→    if (card >= numUsers) {\n   414→      card = 0;\n   415→    }\n   416→    return \"uid:\" + deck.get(card++);\n   417→\n   418→  }\n   419→\n   420→  // Trade implements a card deck approach to selecting\n   421→  // users for trading with tradescenarioservlet\n   422→  private static ArrayList<Integer> deck = null;\n   423→  private static int card = 0;\n   424→\n   425→  /**\n   426→   * This is a convenience method for servlets to set Trade configuration\n   427→   * parameters from servlet initialization parameters. The servlet provides\n   428→   * the init param and its value as strings. This method then parses the\n   429→   * parameter, converts the value to the correct type and sets the\n   430→   * corresponding TradeConfig parameter to the converted value\n   431→   *\n   432→   */\n   433→  public static void setConfigParam(String parm, String value) {\n   434→    Log.log(\"TradeConfig setting parameter: \" + parm + \"=\" + value);\n   435→    // Compare the parm value to valid TradeConfig parameters that can be\n   436→    // set\n   437→    // by servlet initialization\n   438→\n   439→    // First check the proposed new parm and value - if empty or null ignore\n   440→    // it\n   441→    if (parm == null) {\n   442→      return;\n   443→    }\n   444→    parm = parm.trim();\n   445→    if (parm.length() <= 0) {\n   446→      return;\n   447→    }\n   448→    if (value == null) {\n   449→      return;\n   450→    }\n   451→    value = value.trim();\n   452→\n   453→    if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"orderProcessingMode\")) {\n   454→      try {\n   455→        for (int i = 0; i < orderProcessingModeNames.length; i++) {\n   456→          if (value.equalsIgnoreCase(orderProcessingModeNames[i])) {\n   457→            orderProcessingMode = i;\n   458→            break;\n   459→          }\n   460→        }\n   461→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   462→        Log.error(\n   463→            \"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"trying to set orderProcessingMode to \" + value\n   464→                + \"reverting to current value: \" + orderProcessingModeNames[orderProcessingMode],\n   465→            e);\n   466→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   467→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"accessMode\")) {\n   468→      try {\n   469→        for (int i = 0; i < accessModeNames.length; i++) {\n   470→          if (value.equalsIgnoreCase(accessModeNames[i])) {\n   471→            accessMode = i;\n   472→            break;\n   473→          }\n   474→        }\n   475→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   476→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"trying to set accessMode to \" + value\n   477→            + \"reverting to current value: \"\n   478→            + accessModeNames[accessMode], e);\n   479→      }\n   480→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"WebInterface\")) {\n   481→      try {\n   482→        for (int i = 0; i < webInterfaceNames.length; i++) {\n   483→          if (value.equalsIgnoreCase(webInterfaceNames[i])) {\n   484→            webInterface = i;\n   485→            break;\n   486→          }\n   487→        }\n   488→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   489→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"trying to set WebInterface to \" + value\n   490→            + \"reverting to current value: \"\n   491→            + webInterfaceNames[webInterface], e);\n   492→\n   493→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   494→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"maxUsers\")) {\n   495→      try {\n   496→        MAX_USERS = Integer.parseInt(value);\n   497→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   498→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\"\n   499→            + \"Setting maxusers, error parsing string to int:\" + value\n   500→            + \"revering to current value: \" + MAX_USERS, e);\n   501→      } // On error, revert to saved\n   502→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"maxQuotes\")) {\n   503→      try {\n   504→        MAX_QUOTES = Integer.parseInt(value);\n   505→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   506→        // >>rjm\n   507→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(...) minor exception caught\"\n   508→            + \"Setting max_quotes, error parsing string to int \" + value\n   509→            + \"reverting to current value: \" + MAX_QUOTES, e);\n   510→        // <<rjm\n   511→      } // On error, revert to saved\n   512→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"primIterations\")) {\n   513→      try {\n   514→        primIterations = Integer.parseInt(value);\n   515→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   516→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\"\n   517→            + \"Setting primIterations, error parsing string to int:\" + value\n   518→            + \"revering to current value: \" + primIterations, e);\n   519→      } // On error, revert to saved\n   520→    }\n   521→  }\n   522→\n   523→  /**\n   524→   * Gets the orderProcessingModeNames\n   525→   *\n   526→   * @return Returns a String[]\n   527→   */\n   528→  public static String[] getOrderProcessingModeNames() {\n   529→    return orderProcessingModeNames;\n   530→  }\n   531→\n   532→  /**\n   533→   * Gets the webInterfaceNames\n   534→   *\n   535→   * @return Returns a String[]\n   536→   */\n   537→  public static String[] getWebInterfaceNames() {\n   538→    return webInterfaceNames;\n   539→  }\n   540→\n   541→  /**\n   542→   * Gets the webInterfaceNames\n   543→   *\n   544→   * @return Returns a String[]\n   545→   */\n   546→  /*\n   547→   * public static String[] getCachingTypeNames() {\n   548→   * return cachingTypeNames;\n   549→   * }\n   550→   */\n   551→\n   552→  /**\n   553→   * Gets the scenarioMixes\n   554→   *\n   555→   * @return Returns a int[][]\n   556→   */\n   557→  public static int[][] getScenarioMixes() {\n   558→    return scenarioMixes;\n   559→  }\n   560→\n   561→  /**\n   562→   * Gets the mAX_USERS.\n   563→   *\n   564→   * @return Returns a int\n   565→   */\n   566→  public static int getMAX_USERS() {\n   567→    return MAX_USERS;\n   568→  }\n   569→\n   570→  /**\n   571→   * Sets the mAX_USERS.\n   572→   *\n   573→   * @param mAX_USERS\n   574→   *                  The mAX_USERS to set\n   575→   */\n   576→  public static void setMAX_USERS(int mAX_USERS) {\n   577→    MAX_USERS = mAX_USERS;\n   578→    deck = null; // reset the card deck for selecting users\n   579→  }\n   580→\n   581→  /**\n   582→   * Gets the mAX_QUOTES.\n   583→   *\n   584→   * @return Returns a int\n   585→   */\n   586→  public static int getMAX_QUOTES() {\n   587→    return MAX_QUOTES;\n   588→  }\n   589→\n   590→  /**\n   591→   * Sets the mAX_QUOTES.\n   592→   *\n   593→   * @param mAX_QUOTES\n   594→   *                   The mAX_QUOTES to set\n   595→   */\n   596→  public static void setMAX_QUOTES(int mAX_QUOTES) {\n   597→    MAX_QUOTES = mAX_QUOTES;\n   598→  }\n   599→\n   600→  /**\n   601→   * Gets the mAX_HOLDINGS.\n   602→   *\n   603→   * @return Returns a int\n   604→   */\n   605→  public static int getMAX_HOLDINGS() {\n   606→    return MAX_HOLDINGS;\n   607→  }\n   608→\n   609→  /**\n   610→   * Sets the mAX_HOLDINGS.\n   611→   *\n   612→   * @param mAX_HOLDINGS\n   613→   *                     The mAX_HOLDINGS to set\n   614→   */\n   615→  public static void setMAX_HOLDINGS(int mAX_HOLDINGS) {\n   616→    MAX_HOLDINGS = mAX_HOLDINGS;\n   617→  }\n   618→\n   619→  /**\n   620→   * Gets the scenarioCount.\n   621→   *\n   622→   * @return Returns a int\n   623→   */\n   624→  public static int getScenarioCount() {\n   625→    return scenarioCount;\n   626→  }\n   627→\n   628→  /**\n   629→   * Sets the scenarioCount.\n   630→   *\n   631→   * @param scenarioCount\n   632→   *                      The scenarioCount to set\n   633→   */\n   634→  public static void setScenarioCount(int scenarioCount) {\n   635→    TradeConfig.scenarioCount = scenarioCount;\n   636→  }\n   637→\n   638→  public static synchronized void incrementScenarioCount() {\n   639→    scenarioCount++;\n   640→  }\n   641→\n   642→  /**\n   643→   * Gets the jdbc driver needs global transaction Some XA Drivers require a\n   644→   * global transaction to be started for all SQL calls. To work around this,\n   645→   * set this to true to cause the direct mode to start a user transaction.\n   646→   *\n   647→   * @return Returns a boolean\n   648→   */\n   649→  public static boolean getJDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation() {\n   650→    return JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation;\n   651→  }\n   652→\n   653→  /**\n   654→   * Sets the jdbc driver needs global transaction\n   655→   *\n   656→   * @param JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransationVal\n   657→   *                                           the value\n   658→   */\n   659→  public static void setJDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation(boolean JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransationVal) {\n   660→    JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation = JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransationVal;\n   661→  }\n   662→\n   663→  /**\n   664→   * Gets the updateQuotePrices.\n   665→   *\n   666→   * @return Returns a boolean\n   667→   */\n   668→  public static boolean getUpdateQuotePrices() {\n   669→    return updateQuotePrices;\n   670→  }\n   671→\n   672→  /**\n   673→   * Sets the updateQuotePrices.\n   674→   *\n   675→   * @param updateQuotePrices\n   676→   *                          The updateQuotePrices to set\n   677→   */\n   678→  public static void setUpdateQuotePrices(boolean updateQuotePrices) {\n   679→    TradeConfig.updateQuotePrices = updateQuotePrices;\n   680→  }\n   681→\n   682→  public static int getPrimIterations() {\n   683→    return primIterations;\n   684→  }\n   685→\n   686→  public static void setPrimIterations(int iter) {\n   687→    primIterations = iter;\n   688→  }\n   689→\n   690→  public static boolean getLongRun() {\n   691→    return longRun;\n   692→  }\n   693→\n   694→  public static void setLongRun(boolean longRun) {\n   695→    TradeConfig.longRun = longRun;\n   696→  }\n   697→\n   698→  public static void setPublishQuotePriceChange(boolean publishQuotePriceChange) {\n   699→    TradeConfig.publishQuotePriceChange = publishQuotePriceChange;\n   700→  }\n   701→\n   702→  public static boolean getPublishQuotePriceChange() {\n   703→    return publishQuotePriceChange;\n   704→  }\n   705→\n   706→  public static void setMarketSummaryInterval(int seconds) {\n   707→    TradeConfig.marketSummaryInterval = seconds;\n   708→  }\n   709→\n   710→  public static int getMarketSummaryInterval() {\n   711→    return TradeConfig.marketSummaryInterval;\n   712→  }\n   713→\n   714→  public static void setRunTimeMode(int value) {\n   715→    runTimeMode = value;\n   716→  }\n   717→\n   718→  public static int getRunTimeMode() {\n   719→    return runTimeMode;\n   720→  }\n   721→\n   722→  public static void setOrderProcessingMode(int value) {\n   723→    orderProcessingMode = value;\n   724→  }\n   725→\n   726→  public static int getOrderProcessingMode() {\n   727→    return orderProcessingMode;\n   728→  }\n   729→\n   730→  public static void setAccessMode(int value) {\n   731→    accessMode = value;\n   732→  }\n   733→\n   734→  public static int getAccessMode() {\n   735→    return accessMode;\n   736→  }\n   737→\n   738→  public static void setWebInterface(int value) {\n   739→    webInterface = value;\n   740→  }\n   741→\n   742→  public static int getWebInterface() {\n   743→    return webInterface;\n   744→  }\n   745→\n   746→  public static void setDisplayOrderAlerts(boolean value) {\n   747→    displayOrderAlerts = value;\n   748→  }\n   749→\n   750→  public static boolean getDisplayOrderAlerts() {\n   751→    return displayOrderAlerts;\n   752→  }\n   753→\n   754→  public static void setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(int value) {\n   755→    listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = value;\n   756→  }\n   757→\n   758→  public static int getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() {\n   759→    return listQuotePriceChangeFrequency;\n   760→  }\n   761→}\n   762→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"972f618c-b108-451c-ab28-9c26ac30903f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RH4q7C2UGxkbe6n9niDeFA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\n    23→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.events.QuotePriceChangeEvent;\n    27→\n    28→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    29→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    30→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    31→\n    32→/**\n    33→ * This class is a holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary\n    34→ * WebSocket\n    35→ * and the JAX-RS SSE Broadcaster\n    36→ * It fires a CDI event everytime a price change is added\n    37→ **/\n    38→\n    39→@Component\n    40→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList {\n    41→\n    42→  private final List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();\n    43→  private final int maxSize = 5;\n    44→\n    45→  @Autowired\n    46→  ApplicationEventPublisher publisher;\n    47→\n    48→  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    49→\n    50→    int symbolNumber = Integer.parseInt(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    51→\n    52→    if (symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    53→      list.add(0, quoteData);\n    54→\n    55→      // Add stock, remove if needed\n    56→      if (list.size() > maxSize) {\n    57→        list.remove(maxSize);\n    58→      }\n    59→      publisher.publishEvent(new QuotePriceChangeEvent(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol()));\n    60→    }\n    61→    return true;\n    62→  }\n    63→\n    64→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n    65→    return list.isEmpty();\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Size(max = 5)\n    69→  @NotEmpty\n    70→  public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    71→    return list;\n    72→  }\n    73→}\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"3dbd34f3-4fbf-4e4f-9015-040a12f7de88"}
