{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TLqFNdLbtEipsLSQVGEZiT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.support.ApplicationProps;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     6→import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.EnableConfigurationProperties;\n     7→import org.springframework.boot.web.servlet.ServletComponentScan;\n     8→import org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\n     9→\n    10→@ComponentScan\n    11→@SpringBootApplication\n    12→@EnableConfigurationProperties(ApplicationProps.class)\n    13→@ServletComponentScan // Enable support for @WebServlet, @WebFilter, etc.\n    14→public class DaytraderApplication {\n    15→\n    16→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    17→        SpringApplication.run(DaytraderApplication.class, args);\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"ea21cba4-ad2a-4054-91d8-42691fe1d595"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MyNDgyu74MsEHesJWTPvFJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.builder.SpringApplicationBuilder;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.web.servlet.support.SpringBootServletInitializer;\n     5→\n     6→public class ServletInitializer extends SpringBootServletInitializer {\n     7→\n     8→\t@Override\n     9→\tprotected SpringApplicationBuilder configure(SpringApplicationBuilder application) {\n    10→\t\treturn application.sources(DaytraderApplication.class);\n    11→\t}\n    12→\n    13→}\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c19ae2c8-8be6-4c35-8532-5f66952f1290"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Uuuf6AQjkBmQ9yrkDzQeft","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.support;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.ConfigurationProperties;\n     4→\n     5→@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"daytrader\")\n     6→public class ApplicationProps {\n     7→    private int maxQuotes = 1000;\n     8→    private int maxUsers = 500;\n     9→\n    10→    public int getMaxQuotes() {\n    11→        return maxQuotes;\n    12→    }\n    13→\n    14→    public void setMaxQuotes(int maxQuotes) {\n    15→        this.maxQuotes = maxQuotes;\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    public int getMaxUsers() {\n    19→        return maxUsers;\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    public void setMaxUsers(int maxUsers) {\n    23→        this.maxUsers = maxUsers;\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"b822124e-a409-4b7a-8303-e410df40a72f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011qfhydpMhhpmn2vh2oxzsm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.config;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.concurrent.ThreadFactory;\n     4→\n     5→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n     6→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     7→import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;\n     8→import org.springframework.core.task.AsyncTaskExecutor;\n     9→import org.springframework.scheduling.concurrent.ThreadPoolTaskExecutor;\n    10→import org.springframework.scheduling.concurrent.ThreadPoolTaskScheduler;\n    11→\n    12→@Configuration\n    13→@EnableAsync\n    14→public class AsyncConfig {\n    15→\n    16→    @Bean(name = \"ManagedExecutorService\")\n    17→    public AsyncTaskExecutor managedExecutorService() {\n    18→        ThreadPoolTaskExecutor threadPoolTaskExecutor = new ThreadPoolTaskExecutor();\n    19→        threadPoolTaskExecutor.setThreadNamePrefix(\"mes-\");\n    20→        threadPoolTaskExecutor.initialize();\n    21→        return threadPoolTaskExecutor;\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    @Bean(name = \"ManagedScheduledTaskExecutor\")\n    25→    public ThreadPoolTaskScheduler taskScheduler() {\n    26→        ThreadPoolTaskScheduler threadPoolTaskExecutor = new ThreadPoolTaskScheduler();\n    27→        threadPoolTaskExecutor.setThreadNamePrefix(\"mstex-\");\n    28→        threadPoolTaskExecutor.initialize();\n    29→        return threadPoolTaskExecutor;\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @Bean(name = \"ManagedThreadFactory\")\n    33→    public ThreadFactory managedThreadFactoryBean() {\n    34→        return Thread\n    35→                .ofPlatform()\n    36→                .name(\"mes-\", 0) // mes-1, mes-2, ...\n    37→                .uncaughtExceptionHandler((t, e) -> {\n    38→                    // hook into your logger\n    39→                    System.err.println(\"Uncaught in \" + t.getName());\n    40→                    e.printStackTrace();\n    41→                })\n    42→                .factory();\n    43→    }\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c2c9f1a6-ceb9-4a88-b9c4-fb05ea25e53c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GeMF5Nxg2AgHbSDxfH3A29","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.config;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n     4→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     5→import org.springframework.jms.annotation.EnableJms;\n     6→import org.springframework.jms.config.DefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory;\n     7→\n     8→import jakarta.jms.ConnectionFactory;\n     9→\n    10→/**\n    11→ * Replaces Liberty JMS objects (wasJmsServer/Client, queues, topics).\n    12→ * We use embedded Artemis and configure separate factories for queue vs topic.\n    13→ */\n    14→@EnableJms\n    15→@Configuration\n    16→public class JmsConfig {\n    17→\t@Bean\n    18→\tpublic DefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory queueFactory(\n    19→\t\t\tConnectionFactory cf) {\n    20→\t\tDefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory f = new DefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory();\n    21→\t\tf.setConnectionFactory(cf);\n    22→\t\tf.setPubSubDomain(false);\n    23→\t\tf.setSessionTransacted(true);\n    24→\t\treturn f;\n    25→\t}\n    26→\n    27→\t@Bean\n    28→\tpublic DefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory topicFactory(\n    29→\t\t\tConnectionFactory cf) {\n    30→\t\tDefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory f = new DefaultJmsListenerContainerFactory();\n    31→\t\tf.setConnectionFactory(cf);\n    32→\t\tf.setPubSubDomain(true);\n    33→\t\treturn f;\n    34→\t}\n    35→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c3eee8da-edf1-4394-89b6-b786c643ebeb"}
