{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GcgEM28TjGw62QT9rQdKLJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.config;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n     4→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     5→import org.springframework.web.socket.server.standard.ServerEndpointExporter;\n     6→\n     7→@Configuration\n     8→public class WebSocketEndpointConfig {\n     9→\n    10→    @Bean\n    11→    public ServerEndpointExporter serverEndpointExporter() {\n    12→        return new ServerEndpointExporter();\n    13→    }\n    14→}\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"00f8a3ad-13c7-4200-9eff-f28aa2c96d2c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0191KQNJDqXJExx6L4VD5WGK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.config;\n     2→\n     3→import org.apache.catalina.connector.Connector;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.web.embedded.tomcat.TomcatServletWebServerFactory;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.web.server.WebServerFactoryCustomizer;\n     6→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\n     7→import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Expose an additional HTTP connector on 9080 while HTTPS 9443 remains the main\n    11→ * server.port.\n    12→ * Mirrors Liberty's httpPort=9080, httpsPort=9443 setup.\n    13→ */\n    14→@Configuration\n    15→public class DualPortConfig {\n    16→\n    17→    @Bean\n    18→    public WebServerFactoryCustomizer<TomcatServletWebServerFactory> dualPortCustomizer() {\n    19→        return factory -> {\n    20→            Connector http = new Connector(TomcatServletWebServerFactory.DEFAULT_PROTOCOL);\n    21→            http.setPort(9080);\n    22→            factory.addAdditionalTomcatConnectors(http);\n    23→        };\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"55001781-fccb-46ad-afc4-a9ef2cb10701"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FeTbJjxcCDzwHNJt9ihQCi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.websocket.server.ServerEndpointConfig;\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.BeansException;\n     5→import org.springframework.beans.factory.config.AutowireCapableBeanFactory;\n     6→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;\n     7→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware;\n     8→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     9→\n    10→@Component\n    11→public class SpringEndpointConfigurator\n    12→    extends ServerEndpointConfig.Configurator\n    13→    implements ApplicationContextAware {\n    14→\n    15→    private static AutowireCapableBeanFactory beanFactory;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public void setApplicationContext(ApplicationContext ctx)\n    19→        throws BeansException {\n    20→        beanFactory = ctx.getAutowireCapableBeanFactory();\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public <T> T getEndpointInstance(Class<T> endpointClass)\n    25→        throws InstantiationException {\n    26→        // Let Spring construct the endpoint (so constructor injection works)\n    27→        return beanFactory.createBean(endpointClass);\n    28→    }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDBspcMgLodRgiyp5wnvnJ","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"988e4d88-d22d-410c-9aa8-5e6e74154eb2"}
