{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ATPADRhWFdDpGPQQeTA4CG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01C4rHrSENVkJTK5Et1dATLG","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix remaining Spring imports in web files","prompt":"I need you to fix ALL remaining Spring imports across ALL Java files in the DayTrader application at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src\n\nThe migration is Spring Boot -> Quarkus. There are MANY files still using Spring annotations. I need you to:\n\n1. First, search for all files that still contain `org.springframework` imports\n2. For each file, read it and make the following replacements:\n\n### Common Patterns to Replace:\n\n**Imports to remove/replace:**\n- `import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;` -> REMOVE (not needed, servlets use @WebServlet)\n- `import org.springframework.web.context.support.SpringBeanAutowiringSupport;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;` -> `import jakarta.inject.Inject;`\n- `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;` -> `import jakarta.inject.Named;`\n- `import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;` -> `import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;`\n- `import org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;` -> `import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;`\n- `import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.task.AsyncTaskExecutor;` -> `import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;`\n- `import org.springframework.core.task.TaskExecutor;` -> `import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;`\n- `import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.SessionScope;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.env.Environment;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.io.Resource;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.io.ResourceLoader;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.jms.core.JmsTemplate;` -> REMOVE\n\n**Annotation replacements:**\n- `@Component` (Spring) -> Remove annotation (servlets already have @WebServlet) OR replace with `@ApplicationScoped` if it's a CDI bean\n- `@Autowired` -> `@Inject`\n- `@Qualifier(\"...\")` -> `@Named(\"...\")`\n\n**Code replacements:**\n- `SpringBeanAutowiringSupport.processInjectionBasedOnCurrentContext(this);` -> REMOVE THIS LINE (CDI injection is automatic in Quarkus for servlets via @Inject)\n- `SpringBeanAutowiringSupport.processInjectionBasedOnServletContext(this, config.getServletContext());` -> REMOVE THIS LINE\n- For servlets that use `@Autowired` fields, change to `@Inject`\n- For `@SessionScope` on classes, replace with CDI session scoping or remove (make fields session-stored manually)\n\n### Specific Complex Files:\n\n**TradeServletAction.java** - This is complex:\n- Remove `@Component`, `@SessionScope`\n- Replace `@Autowired` with `@Inject`  \n- Replace `ApplicationContext applicationContext` usage: use CDI lookup instead\n- The class uses applicationContext.getBean() to get TradeServices by name. Replace with CDI Instance:\n  - Add field: `@Inject @jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance<com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices> tradeServicesInstance;`\n  - In the `getTradeAction` method, iterate to find the matching impl by name\n\n**OrdersAlertFilter.java** - Replace Spring autowiring:\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n- Use CDI @Inject instead of @Autowired\n- Remove ApplicationContext\n\n**TradeWebContextListener.java** - Replace Spring Environment/ResourceLoader:\n- Use Quarkus/CDI approaches for configuration and resource loading\n- Use `Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResourceAsStream()` for resource loading\n- Use `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.ConfigProvider` for config values\n\n**PingManagedThread.java** and **PingManagedExecutor.java** - Replace Spring task executor:\n- Replace `AsyncTaskExecutor` with `ExecutorService`\n- Replace `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"ManagedExecutorService\")` with `@Inject @Named(\"ManagedExecutorService\")`\n\n**PingJDBCRead.java** - Replace Spring ApplicationContext:\n- Use CDI @Inject directly for DataSource\n\n**PingServlet2MDBQueue.java** and **PingServlet2MDBTopic.java** - JMS servlets:\n- Remove JmsTemplate\n- Make them return a message saying \"JMS disabled in Quarkus migration\"\n\n**PingWebSocketJson.java** - Replace Spring task executor:\n- `TaskExecutor` -> `ExecutorService`  \n- `@Autowired @Qualifier` -> `@Inject @Named`\n\n**MarketSummaryWebSocket.java** and **MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents.java** - WebSocket classes:\n- Replace Spring ApplicationContext with CDI\n- Replace @EventListener with @Observes  \n- Replace @Async with async handling via ExecutorService\n- Replace @Component with @ApplicationScoped\n\n**CDIMethodConstraintBean.java** (beanval):\n- Replace `@Component` + `@RequestScope` with `@jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n\n**PingServletBeanValSimple1.java, PingServletBeanValSimple2.java, PingServletBeanValCDI.java** (beanval):\n- Remove `@Component`, add CDI if needed\n\n**TestServlet.java** - Replace Spring ApplicationContext:\n- Remove ApplicationContext field\n- Use CDI Instance to get beans\n\n**TradeScenarioServlet.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove `@Component`\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**TradeConfigServlet.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove `@Component`\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**PrimFilter.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**TradeAppServlet.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove `@Component`\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**TradeJDBC.java** and **TradeEJB.java** (interfaces):\n- Replace `org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier` with `jakarta.inject.Qualifier`\n\nPlease go through EVERY file that has `org.springframework` imports and fix them. Read each file first before editing. Return a summary of all files changed.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7134,"cache_read_input_tokens":81432,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7134,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1791},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"6044645d-715d-48f3-8603-f09ab17077d0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need you to fix ALL remaining Spring imports across ALL Java files in the DayTrader application at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src\n\nThe migration is Spring Boot -> Quarkus. There are MANY files still using Spring annotations. I need you to:\n\n1. First, search for all files that still contain `org.springframework` imports\n2. For each file, read it and make the following replacements:\n\n### Common Patterns to Replace:\n\n**Imports to remove/replace:**\n- `import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;` -> REMOVE (not needed, servlets use @WebServlet)\n- `import org.springframework.web.context.support.SpringBeanAutowiringSupport;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;` -> `import jakarta.inject.Inject;`\n- `import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;` -> `import jakarta.inject.Named;`\n- `import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;` -> `import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;`\n- `import org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;` -> `import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;`\n- `import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.task.AsyncTaskExecutor;` -> `import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;`\n- `import org.springframework.core.task.TaskExecutor;` -> `import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;`\n- `import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.SessionScope;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.RequestScope;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.env.Environment;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.io.Resource;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.core.io.ResourceLoader;` -> REMOVE\n- `import org.springframework.jms.core.JmsTemplate;` -> REMOVE\n\n**Annotation replacements:**\n- `@Component` (Spring) -> Remove annotation (servlets already have @WebServlet) OR replace with `@ApplicationScoped` if it's a CDI bean\n- `@Autowired` -> `@Inject`\n- `@Qualifier(\"...\")` -> `@Named(\"...\")`\n\n**Code replacements:**\n- `SpringBeanAutowiringSupport.processInjectionBasedOnCurrentContext(this);` -> REMOVE THIS LINE (CDI injection is automatic in Quarkus for servlets via @Inject)\n- `SpringBeanAutowiringSupport.processInjectionBasedOnServletContext(this, config.getServletContext());` -> REMOVE THIS LINE\n- For servlets that use `@Autowired` fields, change to `@Inject`\n- For `@SessionScope` on classes, replace with CDI session scoping or remove (make fields session-stored manually)\n\n### Specific Complex Files:\n\n**TradeServletAction.java** - This is complex:\n- Remove `@Component`, `@SessionScope`\n- Replace `@Autowired` with `@Inject`  \n- Replace `ApplicationContext applicationContext` usage: use CDI lookup instead\n- The class uses applicationContext.getBean() to get TradeServices by name. Replace with CDI Instance:\n  - Add field: `@Inject @jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance<com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices> tradeServicesInstance;`\n  - In the `getTradeAction` method, iterate to find the matching impl by name\n\n**OrdersAlertFilter.java** - Replace Spring autowiring:\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n- Use CDI @Inject instead of @Autowired\n- Remove ApplicationContext\n\n**TradeWebContextListener.java** - Replace Spring Environment/ResourceLoader:\n- Use Quarkus/CDI approaches for configuration and resource loading\n- Use `Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResourceAsStream()` for resource loading\n- Use `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.ConfigProvider` for config values\n\n**PingManagedThread.java** and **PingManagedExecutor.java** - Replace Spring task executor:\n- Replace `AsyncTaskExecutor` with `ExecutorService`\n- Replace `@Autowired @Qualifier(\"ManagedExecutorService\")` with `@Inject @Named(\"ManagedExecutorService\")`\n\n**PingJDBCRead.java** - Replace Spring ApplicationContext:\n- Use CDI @Inject directly for DataSource\n\n**PingServlet2MDBQueue.java** and **PingServlet2MDBTopic.java** - JMS servlets:\n- Remove JmsTemplate\n- Make them return a message saying \"JMS disabled in Quarkus migration\"\n\n**PingWebSocketJson.java** - Replace Spring task executor:\n- `TaskExecutor` -> `ExecutorService`  \n- `@Autowired @Qualifier` -> `@Inject @Named`\n\n**MarketSummaryWebSocket.java** and **MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents.java** - WebSocket classes:\n- Replace Spring ApplicationContext with CDI\n- Replace @EventListener with @Observes  \n- Replace @Async with async handling via ExecutorService\n- Replace @Component with @ApplicationScoped\n\n**CDIMethodConstraintBean.java** (beanval):\n- Replace `@Component` + `@RequestScope` with `@jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n\n**PingServletBeanValSimple1.java, PingServletBeanValSimple2.java, PingServletBeanValCDI.java** (beanval):\n- Remove `@Component`, add CDI if needed\n\n**TestServlet.java** - Replace Spring ApplicationContext:\n- Remove ApplicationContext field\n- Use CDI Instance to get beans\n\n**TradeScenarioServlet.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove `@Component`\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**TradeConfigServlet.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove `@Component`\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**PrimFilter.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**TradeAppServlet.java** - Remove Spring:\n- Remove `@Component`\n- Remove SpringBeanAutowiringSupport\n\n**TradeJDBC.java** and **TradeEJB.java** (interfaces):\n- Replace `org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier` with `jakarta.inject.Qualifier`\n\nPlease go through EVERY file that has `org.springframework` imports and fix them. Read each file first before editing. Return a summary of all files changed."}]},"parent_t