{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HcQgF3c4Aad4Zy3Lv81WAF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2021.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch;\n    21→\n    22→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    23→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;\n    24→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    25→\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.RecentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.SpringEndpointConfigurator;\n    30→\n    31→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n    32→import jakarta.websocket.CloseReason;\n    33→import jakarta.websocket.EndpointConfig;\n    34→import jakarta.websocket.OnClose;\n    35→import jakarta.websocket.OnError;\n    36→import jakarta.websocket.OnMessage;\n    37→import jakarta.websocket.OnOpen;\n    38→import jakarta.websocket.Session;\n    39→import jakarta.websocket.server.ServerEndpoint;\n    40→\n    41→/**\n    42→ * This class is a WebSocket EndPoint that sends the Market Summary in JSON form\n    43→ * and\n    44→ * encodes recent quote price changes when requested or when triggered by CDI\n    45→ * events.\n    46→ **/\n    47→@Component\n    48→@ServerEndpoint(value = \"/marketsummary\", encoders = { QuotePriceChangeListEncoder.class }, decoders = {\n    49→        ActionDecoder.class }, configurator = SpringEndpointConfigurator.class)\n    50→public class MarketSummaryWebSocket {\n    51→\n    52→    @Autowired\n    53→    RecentQuotePriceChangeList recentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    54→\n    55→    //\n    56→    private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    57→\n    58→    @Autowired\n    59→    private ApplicationContext applicationContext;\n    60→\n    61→    @jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct\n    62→    void resolveTradeServices() {\n    63→        String key = com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n    64→        if (applicationContext != null && applicationContext.containsBean(key)) {\n    65→            this.tradeAction = applicationContext.getBean(key, TradeServices.class);\n    66→        }\n    67→        if (this.tradeAction == null) {\n    68→            java.util.Map<String, TradeServices> beans = (applicationContext != null)\n    69→                    ? applicationContext.getBeansOfType(TradeServices.class)\n    70→                    : java.util.Collections.emptyMap();\n    71→            java.util.Set<String> available = beans.keySet();\n    72→            throw new IllegalStateException(\"No TradeServices bean named '\" + key + \"' (available: \" + available + \")\");\n    73→        }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    private static final List<Session> sessions = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();\n    77→    private final CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(1);\n    78→\n    79→    static List<Session> getSessions() {\n    80→        return sessions;\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    @OnOpen\n    84→    public void onOpen(final Session session, EndpointConfig ec) {\n    85→        Log.trace(\n    86→                \"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onOpen -- session -->\" + session + \"<--\");\n    87→\n    88→        sessions.add(session);\n    89→        latch.countDown();\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    @OnMessage\n    93→    public void sendMarketSummary(\n    94→            ActionMessage message,\n    95→            Session currentSession) {\n    96→        String action = message.getDecodedAction();\n    97→\n    98→        Log.trace(\n    99→                \"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary -- received -->\" +\n   100→                        action +\n   101→                        \"<--\");\n   102→\n   103→        // Make sure onopen is finished\n   104→        try {\n   105→            latch.await();\n   106→        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n   107→            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\n   108→            Log.error(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary interrupted\", e);\n   109→            return;\n   110→        } catch (Throwable t) {\n   111→            Log.error(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary await failed\", t);\n   112→            return;\n   113→        }\n   114→\n   115→        if (action != null && action.equals(\"updateMarketSummary\")) {\n   116→            try {\n   117→                JsonObject mkSummary = tradeAction.getMarketSummary().toJSON();\n   118→\n   119→                Log.trace(\n   120→                        \"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary -- sending -->\" +\n   121→                                mkSummary +\n   122→                                \"<--\");\n   123→\n   124→                currentSession.getAsyncRemote().sendText(mkSummary.toString());\n   125→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   126→                Log.error(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:sendMarketSummary error\", e);\n   127→            }\n   128→        } else if (action != null && action.equals(\"updateRecentQuotePriceChange\")) {\n   129→            if (!recentQuotePriceChangeList.isEmpty()) {\n   130→                currentSession\n   131→                        .getAsyncRemote()\n   132→                        .sendObject(recentQuotePriceChangeList.recentList());\n   133→            }\n   134→        }\n   135→    }\n   136→\n   137→    @OnError\n   138→    public void onError(Throwable t, Session currentSession) {\n   139→        Log.trace(\n   140→                \"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onError -- session -->\" +\n   141→                        currentSession +\n   142→                        \"<--\");\n   143→        Log.error(\"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onError\", t);\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    @OnClose\n   147→    public void onClose(Session session, CloseReason reason) {\n   148→        Log.trace(\n   149→                \"MarketSummaryWebSocket:onClose -- session -->\" + session + \"<--\");\n   150→        sessions.remove(session);\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    // Event handling moved to MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents to avoid proxying this endpoint\n   154→}\n   155→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C4rHrSENVkJTK5Et1dATLG","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"1777759f-02f4-44eb-8873-71bfc192f1bb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S8gD3yQrMnf2D3NSZ2PdgM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.websocket;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     5→import org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\n     6→import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\n     7→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     8→\n     9→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.events.MarketSummaryUpdateEvent;\n    10→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.events.QuotePriceChangeEvent;\n    11→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    12→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    13→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.RecentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    14→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    15→\n    16→import jakarta.websocket.Session;\n    17→\n    18→@Component\n    19→public class MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents {\n    20→\n    21→    @Autowired\n    22→    private RecentQuotePriceChangeList recentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    23→\n    24→    @Autowired\n    25→    private org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext applicationContext;\n    26→\n    27→    private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    28→\n    29→    @jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct\n    30→    void resolveTradeServices() {\n    31→        String key = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n    32→        if (applicationContext.containsBean(key)) {\n    33→            this.tradeAction = applicationContext.getBean(key, TradeServices.class);\n    34→        }\n    35→        if (this.tradeAction == null) {\n    36→            java.util.Map<String, TradeServices> beans = applicationContext.getBeansOfType(TradeServices.class);\n    37→            java.util.Set<String> available = beans.keySet();\n    38→            throw new IllegalStateException(\"No TradeServices bean named '\" + key + \"' (available: \" + available + \")\");\n    39→        }\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    @EventListener\n    43→    @Async(\"ManagedExecutorService\")\n    44→    public void onStockChange(QuotePriceChangeEvent quotePriceChangeEvent) {\n    45→        Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents:onStockChange\");\n    46→        quotePriceChangeEvent.payload();\n    47→        for (Session s : MarketSummaryWebSocket.getSessions()) {\n    48→            if (s.isOpen()) {\n    49→                s.getAsyncRemote().sendObject(recentQuotePriceChangeList.recentList());\n    50→            }\n    51→        }\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    @EventListener\n    55→    @Async(\"ManagedExecutorService\")\n    56→    public void onMarketSummaryUpdate(MarketSummaryUpdateEvent marketSummaryUpdateEvent) {\n    57→        Log.trace(\"MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents:onMarketSummaryUpdate\");\n    58→        marketSummaryUpdateEvent.payload();\n    59→        try {\n    60→            jakarta.json.JsonObject mkSummary = tradeAction.getMarketSummary().toJSON();\n    61→            for (Session s : MarketSummaryWebSocket.getSessions()) {\n    62→                if (s.isOpen()) {\n    63→                    s.getAsyncRemote().sendText(mkSummary.toString());\n    64→                }\n    65→            }\n    66→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    67→            Log.error(\"MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents:onMarketSummaryUpdate error\", e);\n    68→        }\n    69→    }\n    70→}\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C4rHrSENVkJTK5Et1dATLG","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"0c39f186-5c3d-45d2-8b12-28f71b95e194"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bs8jLyYB8yZuGdVwSjSJ8T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→import java.io.InputStream;\n     7→import java.util.Properties;\n     8→import org.springframework.core.env.Environment;\n     9→import org.springframework.core.io.Resource;\n    10→import org.springframework.core.io.ResourceLoader;\n    11→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Spring Boot startup initializer for DayTrader config.\n    15→ * In-place replacement for the old ServletContextListener+JSF class.\n    16→ */\n    17→@Component\n    18→public class TradeWebContextListener {\n    19→\n    20→    // same name on purpose\n    21→\n    22→    private final Environment env;\n    23→    private final ResourceLoader resourceLoader;\n    24→\n    25→    public TradeWebContextListener(\n    26→        Environment env,\n    27→        ResourceLoader resourceLoader\n    28→    ) {\n    29→        this.env = env;\n    30→        this.resourceLoader = resourceLoader;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    /** Helper: try ENV first, then application.yml, then legacy properties file */\n    34→    private String s(Properties prop, String... keys) {\n    35→        for (String k : keys) {\n    36→            String v = env.getProperty(k);\n    37→            if (v != null) return v;\n    38→        }\n    39→        for (String k : keys) {\n    40→            String v = prop.getProperty(k);\n    41→            if (v != null) return v;\n    42→        }\n    43→        return null;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    @PostConstruct\n    47→    public void init() {\n    48→        Log.trace(\"TradeWebContextListener initializing (Spring Boot)\");\n    49→\n    50→        // Optional legacy file: classpath:properties/daytrader.properties\n    51→        Properties prop = new Properties();\n    52→        try {\n    53→            Resource res = resourceLoader.getResource(\n    54→                \"classpath:properties/daytrader.properties\"\n    55→            );\n    56→            if (res.exists()) {\n    57→                try (InputStream in = res.getInputStream()) {\n    58→                    prop.load(in);\n    59→                    System.out.println(\n    60→                        \"Settings from daytrader.properties: \" + prop\n    61→                    );\n    62→                }\n    63→            } else {\n    64→                System.out.println(\n    65→                    \"daytrader.properties not found (classpath)\"\n    66→                );\n    67→            }\n    68→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    69→            System.out.println(\"Failed to load daytrader.properties (ignored)\");\n    70→        }\n    71→\n    72→        try {\n    73→            // Mirrors your original precedence but adds daytrader.* YAML keys in between.\n    74→            String rt = s(\n    75→                prop,\n    76→                \"RUNTIME_MODE\",\n    77→                \"daytrader.runtime-mode\",\n    78→                \"runtimeMode\"\n    79→            );\n    80→            if (rt != null) TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode(Integer.parseInt(rt));\n    81→\n    82→            String op = s(\n    83→                prop,\n    84→                \"ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE\",\n    85→                \"daytrader.order-processing-mode\",\n    86→                \"orderProcessingMode\"\n    87→            );\n    88→            if (op != null) TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(\n    89→                Integer.parseInt(op)\n    90→            );\n    91→\n    92→            String mu = s(prop, \"MAX_USERS\", \"daytrader.max-users\", \"maxUsers\");\n    93→            if (mu != null) TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(mu));\n    94→\n    95→            String mq = s(\n    96→                prop,\n    97→                \"MAX_QUOTES\",\n    98→                \"daytrader.max-quotes\",\n    99→                \"maxQuotes\"\n   100→            );\n   101→            if (mq != null) TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(mq));\n   102→\n   103→            String pub = s(\n   104→                prop,\n   105→                \"PUBLISH_QUOTES\",\n   106→                \"daytrader.publish-quotes\",\n   107→                \"publishQuotePriceChange\"\n   108→            );\n   109→            if (pub != null) TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(\n   110→                Boolean.parseBoolean(pub)\n   111→            );\n   112→\n   113→            String alerts = s(\n   114→                prop,\n   115→                \"DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS\",\n   116→                \"daytrader.display-order-alerts\",\n   117→                \"displayOrderAlerts\"\n   118→            );\n   119→            if (alerts != null) TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(\n   120→                Boolean.parseBoolean(alerts)\n   121→            );\n   122→\n   123→            String wi = s(\n   124→                prop,\n   125→                \"WEB_INTERFACE\",\n   126→                \"daytrader.web-interface\",\n   127→                \"webInterface\"\n   128→            );\n   129→            if (wi != null) TradeConfig.setWebInterface(Integer.parseInt(wi));\n   130→\n   131→            String freq = s(\n   132→                prop,\n   133→                \"LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\",\n   134→                \"daytrader.list-quote-price-change-frequency\",\n   135→                \"listQuotePriceChangeFrequency\"\n   136→            );\n   137→            if (freq != null) TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(\n   138→                Integer.parseInt(freq)\n   139→            );\n   140→\n   141→            // File-only in your original code — we also allow YAML keys\n   142→            String prim = s(\n   143→                prop,\n   144→                \"daytrader.prim-iterations\",\n   145→                \"primIterations\"\n   146→            );\n   147→            if (prim != null) TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(\n   148→                Integer.parseInt(prim)\n   149→            );\n   150→\n   151→            String msi = s(\n   152→                prop,\n   153→                \"daytrader.market-summary-interval\",\n   154→                \"marketSummaryInterval\"\n   155→            );\n   156→            if (msi != null) TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(\n   157→                Integer.parseInt(msi)\n   158→            );\n   159→\n   160→            String lr = s(prop, \"daytrader.long-run\", \"longRun\");\n   161→            if (lr != null) TradeConfig.setLongRun(Boolean.parseBoolean(lr));\n   162→\n   163→            System.out.print(\n   164→                \"Running in \" +\n   165→                TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] +\n   166→                \" Mode\"\n   167→            );\n   168→            System.out.print(\n   169→                \" | Order Processing \" +\n   170→                TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()]\n   171→            );\n   172→            System.out.print(\" | MAX_USERS=\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS());\n   173→            System.out.print(\" | MAX_QUOTES=\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES());\n   174→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   175→            Log.error(\"Error initializing TradeConfig\", e);\n   176→        }\n   177→    }\n   178→}\n   179→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C4rHrSENVkJTK5Et1dATLG","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"ec026ffc-787a-4054-8574-904b15b0ad0d"}
