{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DbYZxXeK6DryCmk5pdWj13","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\n    19→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\n    20→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\n    21→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\n    22→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    23→import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n    24→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    25→\n    26→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n    27→\n    28→@Qualifier\n    29→@Retention(RUNTIME)\n    30→@Target({ TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER })\n    31→public @interface TradeJDBC {\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C4rHrSENVkJTK5Et1dATLG","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"5fccc7fb-0a39-4089-8ffa-338e675fe051"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GJFT5GgKiGiWXzgm9qhQCa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    19→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    20→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    21→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    27→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    28→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    29→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.ServletContext;\n    31→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    32→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    33→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    34→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    35→import java.io.IOException;\n    36→import java.io.Serializable;\n    37→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    38→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    39→import java.util.Collection;\n    40→import java.util.Iterator;\n    41→import java.util.Map;\n    42→import org.springframework.web.context.annotation.SessionScope;\n    43→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    44→\n    45→/**\n    46→ * TradeServletAction provides servlet specific client side access to each of\n    47→ * the Trade brokerage user operations. These include login, logout, buy, sell,\n    48→ * getQuote, etc. TradeServletAction manages a web interface to Trade handling\n    49→ * HttpRequests/HttpResponse objects and forwarding results to the appropriate\n    50→ * JSP page for the web interface. TradeServletAction invokes\n    51→ * {@link TradeAction} methods to actually perform each trading operation.\n    52→ *\n    53→ */\n    54→@Component\n    55→@SessionScope\n    56→@Trace\n    57→public class TradeServletAction implements Serializable {\n    58→\n    59→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 7732313125198761455L;\n    60→\n    61→        private TradeServices tAction;\n    62→\n    63→        @Autowired\n    64→        private ApplicationContext applicationContext;\n    65→\n    66→        public TradeServletAction() {\n    67→        }\n    68→\n    69→        @PostConstruct\n    70→        void resolveTradeServices() {\n    71→                String key = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n    72→                if (applicationContext != null && applicationContext.containsBean(key)) {\n    73→                        this.tAction = applicationContext.getBean(key, TradeServices.class);\n    74→                }\n    75→                if (this.tAction == null) {\n    76→                        Map<String, TradeServices> beans = (applicationContext != null)\n    77→                                        ? applicationContext.getBeansOfType(TradeServices.class)\n    78→                                        : java.util.Collections.emptyMap();\n    79→                        java.util.Set<String> available = beans.keySet();\n    80→                        throw new IllegalStateException(\"No TradeServices bean named '\" + key + \"' (available: \" + available + \")\");\n    81→                }\n    82→        }\n    83→\n    84→    /**\n    85→     * Display User Profile information such as address, email, etc. for the\n    86→     * given Trader Dispatch to the Trade Account JSP for display\n    87→     *\n    88→     * @param userID\n    89→     *                The User to display profile info\n    90→     * @param ctx\n    91→     *                the servlet context\n    92→     * @param req\n    93→     *                the HttpRequest object\n    94→     * @param resp\n    95→     *                the HttpResponse object\n    96→     * @param results\n    97→     *                A short description of the results/success of this web request\n    98→     *                provided on the web page\n    99→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   100→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   101→     *                                             is encountered\n   102→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   103→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   104→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   105→     *                                             user\n   106→     *\n   107→     */\n   108→    void doAccount(\n   109→            ServletContext ctx,\n   110→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   111→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   112→            String userID,\n   113→            String results) throws jakarta.servlet.ServletException, java.io.IOException {\n   114→        try {\n   115→            AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.getAccountData(userID);\n   116→            AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = tAction.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   117→            Collection<?> orderDataBeans = (TradeConfig.getLongRun()\n   118→                    ? new ArrayList<Object>()\n   119→                    : (Collection<?>) tAction.getOrders(userID));\n   120→\n   121→            req.setAttribute(\"accountData\", accountData);\n   122→            req.setAttribute(\"accountProfileData\", accountProfileData);\n   123→            req.setAttribute(\"orderDataBeans\", orderDataBeans);\n   124→            req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   125→            requestDispatch(\n   126→                    ctx,\n   127→                    req,\n   128→                    resp,\n   129→                    userID,\n   130→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.ACCOUNT_PAGE));\n   131→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   132→            // this is a user\n   133→            // error so I will\n   134→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   135→            req.setAttribute(\n   136→                    \"results\",\n   137→                    results + \"could not find account for userID = \" + userID);\n   138→            requestDispatch(\n   139→                    ctx,\n   140→                    req,\n   141→                    resp,\n   142→                    userID,\n   143→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   144→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   145→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   146→            Log.error(\n   147→                    \"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\",\n   148→                    \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   149→                    e);\n   150→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   151→            // log the exception with error page\n   152→            throw new ServletException(\n   153→                    \"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\" +\n   154→                            \" exception user =\" +\n   155→                            userID,\n   156→                    e);\n   157→        }\n   158→    }\n   159→\n   160→    /**\n   161→     * Update User Profile information such as address, email, etc. for the\n   162→     * given Trader Dispatch to the Trade Account JSP for display If any in put\n   163→     * is incorrect revert back to the account page w/ an appropriate message\n   164→     *\n   165→     * @param userID\n   166→     *                  The User to upddate profile info\n   167→     * @param password\n   168→     *                  The new User password\n   169→     * @param cpassword\n   170→     *                  Confirm password\n   171→     * @param fullname\n   172→     *                  The new User fullname info\n   173→     * @param address\n   174→     *                  The new User address info\n   175→     * @param cc\n   176→     *                  The new User credit card info\n   177→     * @param email\n   178→     *                  The new User email info\n   179→     * @param ctx\n   180→     *                  the servlet context\n   181→     * @param req\n   182→     *                  the HttpRequest object\n   183→     * @param resp\n   184→     *                  the HttpResponse object\n   185→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   186→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   187→     *                                             is encountered\n   188→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   189→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   190→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   191→     *                                             user\n   192→     *\n   193→     */\n   194→    void doAccountUpdate(\n   195→            ServletContext ctx,\n   196→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   197→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   198→            String userID,\n   199→            String password,\n   200→            String cpassword,\n   201→            String fullName,\n   202→            String address,\n   203→            String creditcard,\n   204→            String email) throws jakarta.servlet.ServletException, java.io.IOException {\n   205→        String results = \"\";\n   206→\n   207→        // First verify input data\n   208→        boolean doUpdate = true;\n   209→        if (password.equals(cpassword) == false) {\n   210→            results = \"Update profile error: passwords do not match\";\n   211→            doUpdate = false;\n   212→        } else if (password.length() <= 0 ||\n   213→                fullName.length() <= 0 ||\n   214→                address.length() <= 0 ||\n   215→                creditcard.length() <= 0 ||\n   216→                email.length() <= 0) {\n   217→            results = \"Update profile error: please fill in all profile information fields\";\n   218→            doUpdate = false;\n   219→        }\n   220→        AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = new AccountProfileDataBean(\n   221→                userID,\n   222→                password,\n   223→                fullName,\n   224→                address,\n   225→                email,\n   226→                creditcard);\n   227→        try {\n   228→            if (doUpdate) {\n   229→                accountProfileData = tAction.updateAccountProfile(\n   230→                        accountProfileData);\n   231→                results = \"Account profile update successful\";\n   232→            }\n   233→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   234→            // this is a user\n   235→            // error so I will\n   236→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   237→            req.setAttribute(\n   238→                    \"results\",\n   239→                    results +\n   240→                            \"invalid argument, check userID is correct, and the database is populated\" +\n   241→                            userID);\n   242→            Log.error(\n   243→                    e,\n   244→                    \"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\",\n   245→                    \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   246→                    \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   247→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   248→            // log the exception with error page\n   249→            throw new ServletException(\n   250→                    \"TradeServletAction.doAccountUpdate(...)\" +\n   251→                            \" exception user =\" +\n   252→                            userID,\n   253→                    e);\n   254→        }\n   255→        doAccount(ctx, req, resp, userID, results);\n   256→    }\n   257→\n   258→    /**\n   259→     * Buy a new holding of shares for the given trader Dispatch to the Trade\n   260→     * Portfolio JSP for display\n   261→     *\n   262→     * @param userID\n   263→     *               The User buying shares\n   264→     * @param symbol\n   265→     *               The stock to purchase\n   266→     * @param amount\n   267→     *               The quantity of shares to purchase\n   268→     * @param ctx\n   269→     *               the servlet context\n   270→     * @param req\n   271→     *               the HttpRequest object\n   272→     * @param resp\n   273→     *               the HttpResponse object\n   274→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   275→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   276→     *                                             is encountered\n   277→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   278→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   279→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   280→     *                                             user\n   281→     *\n   282→     */\n   283→    void doBuy(\n   284→            ServletContext ctx,\n   285→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   286→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   287→            String userID,\n   288→            String symbol,\n   289→            String quantity) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   290→        String results = \"\";\n   291→\n   292→        try {\n   293→            OrderDataBean orderData = tAction.buy(\n   294→                    userID,\n   295→                    symbol,\n   296→                    new Double(quantity).doubleValue(),\n   297→                    TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   298→\n   299→            req.setAttribute(\"orderData\", orderData);\n   300→            req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   301→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   302→            // this is a user\n   303→            // error so I will\n   304→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   305→            req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"illegal argument:\");\n   306→            requestDispatch(\n   307→                    ctx,\n   308→                    req,\n   309→                    resp,\n   310→                    userID,\n   311→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   312→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   313→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   314→            Log.error(\n   315→                    e,\n   316→                    \"TradeServletAction.doBuy(...)\",\n   317→                    \"illegal argument. userID = \" + userID,\n   318→                    \"symbol = \" + symbol);\n   319→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   320→            // log the exception with error page\n   321→            throw new ServletException(\n   322→                    \"TradeServletAction.buy(...)\" +\n   323→                            \" exception buying stock \" +\n   324→                            symbol +\n   325→                            \" for user \" +\n   326→                            userID,\n   327→                    e);\n   328→        }\n   329→        requestDispatch(\n   330→                ctx,\n   331→                req,\n   332→                resp,\n   333→                userID,\n   334→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.ORDER_PAGE));\n   335→    }\n   336→\n   337→    /**\n   338→     * Create the Trade Home page with personalized information such as the\n   339→     * traders account balance Dispatch to the Trade Home JSP for display\n   340→     *\n   341→     * @param ctx\n   342→     *                the servlet context\n   343→     * @param req\n   344→     *                the HttpRequest object\n   345→     * @param resp\n   346→     *                the HttpResponse object\n   347→     * @param results\n   348→     *                A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   349→     *                provided on the web page\n   350→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   351→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   352→     *                                             is encountered\n   353→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   354→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   355→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   356→     *                                             user\n   357→     *\n   358→     */\n   359→    void doHome(\n   360→            ServletContext ctx,\n   361→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   362→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   363→            String userID,\n   364→            String results) throws jakarta.servlet.ServletException, java.io.IOException {\n   365→        try {\n   366→            AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.getAccountData(userID);\n   367→            Collection<?> holdingDataBeans = tAction.getHoldings(userID);\n   368→\n   369→            // Edge Caching:\n   370→            // Getting the MarketSummary has been moved to the JSP\n   371→            // MarketSummary.jsp. This makes the MarketSummary a\n   372→            // standalone \"fragment\", and thus is a candidate for\n   373→            // Edge caching.\n   374→            // marketSummaryData = tAction.getMarketSummary();\n   375→\n   376→            req.setAttribute(\"accountData\", accountData);\n   377→            req.setAttribute(\"holdingDataBeans\", holdingDataBeans);\n   378→            // See Edge Caching above\n   379→            // req.setAttribute(\"marketSummaryData\", marketSummaryData);\n   380→            req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   381→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   382→            // this is a user\n   383→            // error so I will\n   384→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   385→            req.setAttribute(\n   386→                    \"results\",\n   387→                    results +\n   388→                            \"check userID = \" +\n   389→                            userID +\n   390→                            \" and that the database is populated\");\n   391→            requestDispatch(\n   392→                    ctx,\n   393→                    req,\n   394→                    resp,\n   395→                    userID,\n   396→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   397→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   398→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   399→            Log.error(\n   400→                    \"TradeServletAction.doHome(...)\" +\n   401→                            \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\" +\n   402→                            \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\",\n   403→                    e);\n   404→        } catch (jakarta.persistence.EntityNotFoundException e) {\n   405→            // this is a user error so I will\n   406→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   407→            req.setAttribute(\n   408→                    \"results\",\n   409→                    results + \"\\nCould not find account for + \" + userID);\n   410→            // requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp,\n   411→            // TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   412→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   413→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   414→            Log.error(\n   415→                    \"TradeServletAction.doHome(...)\" +\n   416→                            \"Error finding account for user \" +\n   417→                            userID +\n   418→                            \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\",\n   419→                    e);\n   420→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   421→            // log the exception with error page\n   422→            throw new ServletException(\n   423→                    \"TradeServletAction.doHome(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID,\n   424→                    e);\n   425→        }\n   426→\n   427→        requestDispatch(\n   428→                ctx,\n   429→                req,\n   430→                resp,\n   431→                userID,\n   432→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   433→    }\n   434→\n   435→    /**\n   436→     * Login a Trade User. Dispatch to the Trade Home JSP for display\n   437→     *\n   438→     * @param userID\n   439→     *                The User to login\n   440→     * @param passwd\n   441→     *                The password supplied by the trader used to authenticate\n   442→     * @param ctx\n   443→     *                the servlet context\n   444→     * @param req\n   445→     *                the HttpRequest object\n   446→     * @param resp\n   447→     *                the HttpResponse object\n   448→     * @param results\n   449→     *                A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   450→     *                provided on the web page\n   451→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   452→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   453→     *                                             is encountered\n   454→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   455→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   456→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   457→     *                                             user\n   458→     *\n   459→     */\n   460→    void doLogin(\n   461→            ServletContext ctx,\n   462→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   463→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   464→            String userID,\n   465→            String passwd) throws jakarta.servlet.ServletException, java.io.IOException {\n   466→        String results = \"\";\n   467→        try {\n   468→            // Got a valid userID and passwd, attempt login\n   469→            if (tAction == null) {\n   470→                System.out.println(\"null\");\n   471→            }\n   472→            AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.login(userID, passwd);\n   473→\n   474→            if (accountData != null) {\n   475→                HttpSession session = req.getSession(true);\n   476→                session.setAttribute(\"uidBean\", userID);\n   477→                session.setAttribute(\n   478→                        \"sessionCreationDate\",\n   479→                        new java.util.Date());\n   480→\n   481→                results = \"Ready to Trade\";\n   482→                doHome(ctx, req, resp, userID, results);\n   483→                return;\n   484→            } else {\n   485→                req.setAttribute(\n   486→                        \"results\",\n   487→                        results + \"\\nCould not find account for + \" + userID);\n   488→                // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means,\n   489→                // handled exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   490→                Log.log(\n   491→                        \"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\",\n   492→                        \"Error finding account for user \" + userID + \"\",\n   493→                        \"user entered a bad username or the database is not populated\");\n   494→            }\n   495→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   496→            // this is a user\n   497→            // error so I will\n   498→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   499→            req.setAttribute(\n   500→                    \"results\",\n   501→                    results + \"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   502→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   503→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   504→            Log.error(\n   505→                    e,\n   506→                    \"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\",\n   507→                    \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   508→                    \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   509→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   510→            // log the exception with error page\n   511→            throw new ServletException(\n   512→                    \"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\" +\n   513→                            \"Exception logging in user \" +\n   514→                            userID +\n   515→                            \"with password\" +\n   516→                            passwd,\n   517→                    e);\n   518→        }\n   519→\n   520→        requestDispatch(\n   521→                ctx,\n   522→                req,\n   523→                resp,\n   524→                userID,\n   525→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.WELCOME_PAGE));\n   526→    }\n   527→\n   528→    /**\n   529→     * Logout a Trade User Dispatch to the Trade Welcome JSP for display\n   530→     *\n   531→     * @param userID\n   532→     *                The User to logout\n   533→     * @param ctx\n   534→     *                the servlet context\n   535→     * @param req\n   536→     *                the HttpRequest object\n   537→     * @param resp\n   538→     *                the HttpResponse object\n   539→     * @param results\n   540→     *                A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   541→     *                provided on the web page\n   542→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   543→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   544→     *                                             is encountered\n   545→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   546→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   547→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   548→     *                                             user\n   549→     *\n   550→     */\n   551→    void doLogout(\n   552→            ServletContext ctx,\n   553→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   554→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   555→            String userID) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   556→        String results = \"\";\n   557→\n   558→        try {\n   559→            tAction.logout(userID);\n   560→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   561→            // this is a user\n   562→            // error so I will\n   563→            // forward them to another page, at the end of the page.\n   564→            req.setAttribute(\n   565→                    \"results\",\n   566→                    results + \"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   567→\n   568→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   569→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   570→            Log.error(\n   571→                    e,\n   572→                    \"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...)\",\n   573→                    \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   574→                    \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   575→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   576→            // log the exception and foward to a error page\n   577→            Log.error(\n   578→                    e,\n   579→                    \"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...):\",\n   580→                    \"Error logging out\" + userID,\n   581→                    \"fowarding to an error page\");\n   582→            // set the status_code to 500\n   583→            throw new ServletException(\n   584→                    \"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...)\" +\n   585→                            \"exception logging out user \" +\n   586→                            userID,\n   587→                    e);\n   588→        }\n   589→        HttpSession session = req.getSession();\n   590→        if (session != null) {\n   591→            session.invalidate();\n   592→        }\n   593→\n   594→        // Added to actually remove a user from the authentication cache\n   595→        req.logout();\n   596→\n   597→        Object o = req.getAttribute(\"TSS-RecreateSessionInLogout\");\n   598→        if (o != null && ((Boolean) o).equals(Boolean.TRUE)) {\n   599→            // Recreate Session object before writing output to the response\n   600→            // Once the response headers are written back to the client the\n   601→            // opportunity\n   602→            // to create a new session in this request may be lost\n   603→            // This is to handle only the TradeScenarioServlet case\n   604→            session = req.getSession(true);\n   605→        }\n   606→        requestDispatch(\n   607→                ctx,\n   608→                req,\n   609→                resp,\n   610→                userID,\n   611→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.WELCOME_PAGE));\n   612→    }\n   613→\n   614→    /**\n   615→     * Retrieve the current portfolio of stock holdings for the given trader\n   616→     * Dispatch to the Trade Portfolio JSP for display\n   617→     *\n   618→     * @param userID\n   619→     *                The User requesting to view their portfolio\n   620→     * @param ctx\n   621→     *                the servlet context\n   622→     * @param req\n   623→     *                the HttpRequest object\n   624→     * @param resp\n   625→     *                the HttpResponse object\n   626→     * @param results\n   627→     *                A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   628→     *                provided on the web page\n   629→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   630→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   631→     *                                             is encountered\n   632→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   633→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   634→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   635→     *                                             user\n   636→     *\n   637→     */\n   638→    void doPortfolio(\n   639→            ServletContext ctx,\n   640→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   641→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   642→            String userID,\n   643→            String results) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   644→        try {\n   645→            // Get the holdiings for this user\n   646→\n   647→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n   648→            Collection<?> holdingDataBeans = tAction.getHoldings(userID);\n   649→\n   650→            // Walk through the collection of user\n   651→            // holdings and creating a list of quotes\n   652→            if (holdingDataBeans.size() > 0) {\n   653→                Iterator<?> it = holdingDataBeans.iterator();\n   654→                while (it.hasNext()) {\n   655→                    HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) it.next();\n   656→                    QuoteDataBean quoteData = tAction.getQuote(\n   657→                            holdingData.getQuoteID());\n   658→                    quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n   659→                }\n   660→            } else {\n   661→                results = results + \".  Your portfolio is empty.\";\n   662→            }\n   663→            req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   664→            req.setAttribute(\"holdingDataBeans\", holdingDataBeans);\n   665→            req.setAttribute(\"quoteDataBeans\", quoteDataBeans);\n   666→            requestDispatch(\n   667→                    ctx,\n   668→                    req,\n   669→                    resp,\n   670→                    userID,\n   671→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.PORTFOLIO_PAGE));\n   672→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   673→            // this is a user\n   674→            // error so I will\n   675→            // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   676→            req.setAttribute(\n   677→                    \"results\",\n   678→                    results + \"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   679→            requestDispatch(\n   680→                    ctx,\n   681→                    req,\n   682→                    resp,\n   683→                    userID,\n   684→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.PORTFOLIO_PAGE));\n   685→            // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   686→            // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   687→            Log.error(\n   688→                    e,\n   689→                    \"TradeServletAction.doPortfolio(...)\",\n   690→                    \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   691→                    \"user error\");\n   692→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   693→            // log the exception with error page\n   694→            throw new ServletException(\n   695→                    \"TradeServletAction.doPortfolio(...)\" +\n   696→                            \" exception user =\" +\n   697→                            userID,\n   698→                    e);\n   699→        }\n   700→    }\n   701→\n   702→    /**\n   703→     * Retrieve the current Quote for the given stock symbol Dispatch to the\n   704→     * Trade Quote JSP for display\n   705→     *\n   706→     * @param userID\n   707→     *               The stock symbol used to get the current quote\n   708→     * @param ctx\n   709→     *               the servlet context\n   710→     * @param req\n   711→     *               the HttpRequest object\n   712→     * @param resp\n   713→     *               the HttpResponse object\n   714→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   715→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   716→     *                                             is encountered\n   717→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   718→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   719→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   720→     *                                             user\n   721→     *\n   722→     */\n   723→    void doQuotes(\n   724→            ServletContext ctx,\n   725→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   726→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   727→            String userID,\n   728→            String symbols) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   729→        try {\n   730→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n   731→            String[] symbolsSplit = symbols.split(\",\");\n   732→            for (String symbol : symbolsSplit) {\n   733→                QuoteDataBean quoteData = tAction.getQuote(symbol.trim());\n   734→                quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n   735→            }\n   736→            req.setAttribute(\"quoteDataBeans\", quoteDataBeans);\n   737→            requestDispatch(\n   738→                    ctx,\n   739→                    req,\n   740→                    resp,\n   741→                    userID,\n   742→                    TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.QUOTE_PAGE));\n   743→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   744→            // log the exception with error page\n   745→            throw new ServletException(\n   746→                    \"TradeServletAction.doQuotes(...)\" +\n   747→                            \" exception user =\" +\n   748→                            userID,\n   749→                    e);\n   750→        }\n   751→    }\n   752→\n   753→    /**\n   754→     * Register a new trader given the provided user Profile information such as\n   755→     * address, email, etc. Dispatch to the Trade Home JSP for display\n   756→     *\n   757→     * @param userID\n   758→     *                 The User to create\n   759→     * @param passwd\n   760→     *                 The User password\n   761→     * @param fullname\n   762→     *                 The new User fullname info\n   763→     * @param ccn\n   764→     *                 The new User credit card info\n   765→     * @param money\n   766→     *                 The new User opening account balance\n   767→     * @param address\n   768→     *                 The new User address info\n   769→     * @param email\n   770→     *                 The new User email info\n   771→     * @return The userID of the new trader\n   772→     * @param ctx\n   773→     *             the servlet context\n   774→     * @param req\n   775→     *             the HttpRequest object\n   776→     * @param resp\n   777→     *             the HttpResponse object\n   778→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   779→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   780→     *                                             is encountered\n   781→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   782→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   783→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   784→     *                                             user\n   785→     *\n   786→     */\n   787→    void doRegister(\n   788→            ServletContext ctx,\n   789→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   790→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   791→            String userID,\n   792→            String passwd,\n   793→            String cpasswd,\n   794→            String fullname,\n   795→            String ccn,\n   796→            String openBalanceString,\n   797→            String email,\n   798→            String address) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   799→        String results = \"\";\n   800→\n   801→        try {\n   802→            // Validate user passwords match and are atleast 1 char in length\n   803→            if ((passwd.equals(cpasswd)) && (passwd.length() >= 1)) {\n   804→                AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.register(\n   805→                        userID,\n   806→                        passwd,\n   807→                        fullname,\n   808→                        address,\n   809→                        email,\n   810→                        ccn,\n   811→                        new BigDecimal(openBalanceString));\n   812→                if (accountData == null) {\n   813→                    results = \"Registration operation failed;\";\n   814→                    System.out.println(results);\n   815→                    req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   816→                    requestDispatch(\n   817→                            ctx,\n   818→                            req,\n   819→                            resp,\n   820→                            userID,\n   821→                            TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.REGISTER_PAGE));\n   822→                } else {\n   823→                    doLogin(ctx, req, resp, userID, passwd);\n   824→                    results = \"Registration operation succeeded;  Account \" +\n   825→                            accountData.getAccountID() +\n   826→                            \" has been created.\";\n   827→                    req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   828→                }\n   829→            } else {\n   830→                // Password validation failed\n   831→                results = \"Registration operation failed, your passwords did not match\";\n   832→                System.out.println(results);\n   833→                req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   834→                requestDispatch(\n   835→                        ctx,\n   836→                        req,\n   837→                        resp,\n   838→                        userID,\n   839→                        TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.REGISTER_PAGE));\n   840→            }\n   841→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   842→            // log the exception with error page\n   843→            throw new ServletException(\n   844→                    \"TradeServletAction.doRegister(...)\" +\n   845→                            \" exception user =\" +\n   846→                            userID,\n   847→                    e);\n   848→        }\n   849→    }\n   850→\n   851→    /**\n   852→     * Sell a current holding of stock shares for the given trader. Dispatch to\n   853→     * the Trade Portfolio JSP for display\n   854→     *\n   855→     * @param userID\n   856→     *               The User buying shares\n   857→     * @param symbol\n   858→     *               The stock to sell\n   859→     * @param indx\n   860→     *               The unique index identifying the users holding to sell\n   861→     * @param ctx\n   862→     *               the servlet context\n   863→     * @param req\n   864→     *               the HttpRequest object\n   865→     * @param resp\n   866→     *               the HttpResponse object\n   867→     * @exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException\n   868→     *                                             If a servlet specific exception\n   869→     *                                             is encountered\n   870→     * @exception jakarta.io.IOException\n   871→     *                                             If an exception occurs while\n   872→     *                                             writing results back to the\n   873→     *                                             user\n   874→     *\n   875→     */\n   876→    void doSell(\n   877→            ServletContext ctx,\n   878→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   879→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   880→            String userID,\n   881→            Integer holdingID) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   882→        String results = \"\";\n   883→        try {\n   884→            OrderDataBean orderData = tAction.sell(\n   885→                    userID,\n   886→                    holdingID,\n   887→                    TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   888→\n   889→            req.setAttribute(\"orderData\", orderData);\n   890→            req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   891→        } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) {\n   892→            // this is a user\n   893→            // error so I will\n   894→            // just log the exception and then later on I will redisplay the\n   895→            // portfolio page\n   896→            // because this is just a user exception\n   897→            Log.error(\n   898→                    e,\n   899→                    \"TradeServletAction.doSell(...)\",\n   900→                    \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   901→                    \"user error\");\n   902→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   903→            // log the exception with error page\n   904→            throw new ServletException(\n   905→                    \"TradeServletAction.doSell(...)\" +\n   906→                            \" exception selling holding \" +\n   907→                            holdingID +\n   908→                            \" for user =\" +\n   909→                            userID,\n   910→                    e);\n   911→        }\n   912→        requestDispatch(\n   913→                ctx,\n   914→                req,\n   915→                resp,\n   916→                userID,\n   917→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.ORDER_PAGE));\n   918→    }\n   919→\n   920→    void doWelcome(\n   921→            ServletContext ctx,\n   922→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   923→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   924→            String status) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   925→        req.setAttribute(\"results\", status);\n   926→        requestDispatch(\n   927→                ctx,\n   928→                req,\n   929→                resp,\n   930→                null,\n   931→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.WELCOME_PAGE));\n   932→    }\n   933→\n   934→    private void requestDispatch(\n   935→            ServletContext ctx,\n   936→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   937→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   938→            String userID,\n   939→            String page) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   940→        ctx.getRequestDispatcher(page).include(req, resp);\n   941→    }\n   942→\n   943→    void doMarketSummary(\n   944→            ServletContext ctx,\n   945→            HttpServletRequest req,\n   946→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n   947→            String userID) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   948→        req.setAttribute(\"results\", \"test\");\n   949→        requestDispatch(\n   950→                ctx,\n   951→                req,\n   952→                resp,\n   953→                userID,\n   954→                TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.MARKET_SUMMARY_PAGE));\n   955→    }\n   956→}\n   957→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C4rHrSENVkJTK5Et1dATLG","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"50d79eb9-0234-4a91-8126-2b9f4231f1f9"}
