{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VdyVAAPeupvYm5uRpWXVVn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The application compiled successfully! The runtime error is because the `@Named` annotations on the TradeServices beans are not being picked up by the CDI proxy classes. The error says: `No TradeServices bean named 'Full EJB3' (available: [directSLSBBean_ClientProxy, tradeDirect_ClientProxy, tradeSLSBBean_ClientProxy])`.\n\nThe problem is that in `getBeanName()`, `ts.getClass()` returns the CDI proxy class, not the original class, so `@Named` annotation isn't found. I need to fix the bean lookup logic. Let me also check and fix the `OrdersAlertFilter` which is the actual point of failure."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3158,"cache_read_input_tokens":128599,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3158,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":289},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"60d587c0-c179-4c95-ab68-4e14eea6ba10"}
