{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JgvDJcdg34u2dAMbhT3pAv","type":"tool_result","content":"Found 6 files\nsrc/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeServletAction.java\nsrc/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/prims/PingJDBCRead.java\nsrc/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TestServlet.java\nsrc/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/OrdersAlertFilter.java\nsrc/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents.java\nsrc/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocket.java"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"47651956-459b-4230-b568-ca43f8f479d5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019FqhTFAFkWTnDYqTLqxa56","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to fix all 6 files plus the AsyncScheduledOrder. The fix is to look at superclass for proxy classes. Let me do all of them:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":676,"cache_read_input_tokens":134131,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":676,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1213},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"26d745a7-9df0-4142-959a-abf9958f9347"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019FqhTFAFkWTnDYqTLqxa56","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01QKeyQ4BpSm5BW7WsGAm5Tf","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix CDI proxy getBeanName in all files","prompt":"I need to fix the `getBeanName()` method across 6 files in the DayTrader project at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src\n\nThe problem: When CDI creates proxy beans in Quarkus, `ts.getClass()` returns a proxy class like `TradeSLSBBean_ClientProxy`, NOT the actual class. So `@Named` annotations are NOT found on the proxy class. The fix is to check `getClass().getSuperclass()` as well.\n\nThe files that contain `getBeanName` method are:\n1. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeServletAction.java\n2. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/OrdersAlertFilter.java\n3. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TestServlet.java\n4. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/prims/PingJDBCRead.java\n5. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents.java\n6. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocket.java\n\nAlso fix:\n7. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java - uses the same pattern\n\nFor each file, read it, find the `getBeanName` method (or equivalent), and replace it with this corrected version:\n\n```java\n    private String getBeanName(TradeServices ts) {\n        // CDI proxy classes need getSuperclass() to find the actual class with annotations\n        Class<?> clazz = ts.getClass();\n        jakarta.inject.Named named = clazz.getAnnotation(jakarta.inject.Named.class);\n        if (named == null && clazz.getSuperclass() != null) {\n            named = clazz.getSuperclass().getAnnotation(jakarta.inject.Named.class);\n        }\n        if (named != null && !named.value().isEmpty()) {\n            return named.value();\n        }\n        // Check superclass for qualifier annotations too\n        Class<?> realClass = clazz;\n        if (realClass.getSuperclass() != null && realClass.getSuperclass() != Object.class) {\n            realClass = realClass.getSuperclass();\n        }\n        if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC.class) != null) {\n            return \"Direct (JDBC)\";\n        }\n        if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB.class) != null) {\n            return \"Full EJB3\";\n        }\n        if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeSession2Direct.class) != null) {\n            return \"Session to Direct\";\n        }\n        // Default to simple class name\n        String simpleName = realClass.getSimpleName();\n        return simpleName;\n    }\n```\n\nFor `AsyncScheduledOrder.java`, the `getTradeService()` method uses a similar pattern. Fix it similarly:\n```java\n    private TradeServices getTradeService() {\n        String key = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n        for (TradeServices ts : tradeServicesInstance) {\n            Class<?> clazz = ts.getClass();\n            Named named = clazz.getAnnotation(Named.class);\n            if (named == null && clazz.getSuperclass() != null) {\n                named = clazz.getSuperclass().getAnnotation(Named.class);\n            }\n            if (named != null && key.equals(named.value())) {\n                return ts;\n            }\n        }\n        // Fallback: return first available\n        return tradeServicesInstance.iterator().next();\n    }\n```\n\nRead each file first before making changes. Return a list of all files changed.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":676,"cache_read_input_tokens":134131,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":676,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1213},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c9d2df64-b1e2-4481-87c4-e9ce92e5e23f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to fix the `getBeanName()` method across 6 files in the DayTrader project at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src\n\nThe problem: When CDI creates proxy beans in Quarkus, `ts.getClass()` returns a proxy class like `TradeSLSBBean_ClientProxy`, NOT the actual class. So `@Named` annotations are NOT found on the proxy class. The fix is to check `getClass().getSuperclass()` as well.\n\nThe files that contain `getBeanName` method are:\n1. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeServletAction.java\n2. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/OrdersAlertFilter.java\n3. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TestServlet.java\n4. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/prims/PingJDBCRead.java\n5. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents.java\n6. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocket.java\n\nAlso fix:\n7. src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java - uses the same pattern\n\nFor each file, read it, find the `getBeanName` method (or equivalent), and replace it with this corrected version:\n\n```java\n    private String getBeanName(TradeServices ts) {\n        // CDI proxy classes need getSuperclass() to find the actual class with annotations\n        Class<?> clazz = ts.getClass();\n        jakarta.inject.Named named = clazz.getAnnotation(jakarta.inject.Named.class);\n        if (named == null && clazz.getSuperclass() != null) {\n            named = clazz.getSuperclass().getAnnotation(jakarta.inject.Named.class);\n        }\n        if (named != null && !named.value().isEmpty()) {\n            return named.value();\n        }\n        // Check superclass for qualifier annotations too\n        Class<?> realClass = clazz;\n        if (realClass.getSuperclass() != null && realClass.getSuperclass() != Object.class) {\n            realClass = realClass.getSuperclass();\n        }\n        if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC.class) != null) {\n            return \"Direct (JDBC)\";\n        }\n        if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB.class) != null) {\n            return \"Full EJB3\";\n        }\n        if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeSession2Direct.class) != null) {\n            return \"Session to Direct\";\n        }\n        // Default to simple class name\n        String simpleName = realClass.getSimpleName();\n        return simpleName;\n    }\n```\n\nFor `AsyncScheduledOrder.java`, the `getTradeService()` method uses a similar pattern. Fix it similarly:\n```java\n    private TradeServices getTradeService() {\n        String key = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n        for (TradeServices ts : tradeServicesInstance) {\n            Class<?> clazz = ts.getClass();\n            Named named = clazz.getAnnotation(Named.class);\n            if (named == null && clazz.getSuperclass() != null) {\n                named = clazz.getSuperclass().getAnnotation(Named.class);\n            }\n            if (named != null && key.equals(named.value())) {\n                return ts;\n            }\n        }\n        // Fallback: return first available\n        return tradeServicesInstance.iterator().next();\n    }\n```\n\nRead each file first before making changes. Return a list of all files changed."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QKeyQ4BpSm5BW7WsGAm5Tf","session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"cb927cfb-ffd7-42e5-b683-b2628539f5e9"}
