{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QKeyQ4BpSm5BW7WsGAm5Tf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All files have been successfully updated with the CDI proxy-aware annotation lookup logic. \n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully fixed the `getBeanName()` method across all 7 files in the DayTrader project to handle CDI proxy beans correctly. The issue was that when CDI creates proxy beans in Quarkus, `ts.getClass()` returns a proxy class (like `TradeSLSBBean_ClientProxy`) instead of the actual class, and the `@Named` annotations are not found on the proxy class.\n\n### Files Changed:\n\n1. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeServletAction.java**\n   - Updated `getBeanName()` method to check superclass for annotations\n\n2. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/OrdersAlertFilter.java**\n   - Updated `getBeanName()` method to check superclass for annotations\n\n3. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TestServlet.java**\n   - Updated `getBeanName()` method to check superclass for annotations\n\n4. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/prims/PingJDBCRead.java**\n   - Updated `getBeanName()` method to check superclass for annotations\n\n5. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocketEvents.java**\n   - Updated `getBeanName()` method to check superclass for annotations\n\n6. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/MarketSummaryWebSocket.java**\n   - Updated `getBeanName()` method to check superclass for annotations\n\n7. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java**\n   - Updated `getTradeService()` method to check superclass for @Named annotation\n\n### Key Changes:\n\n- All methods now check `clazz.getSuperclass()` when the annotation is not found on the proxy class itself\n- Qualifier annotations (`@TradeJDBC`, `@TradeEJB`, `@TradeSession2Direct`) are also checked on the superclass\n- Return values have been standardized to match expected bean names (e.g., \"Direct (JDBC)\", \"Full EJB3\", \"Session to Direct\")\n- The logic now uses `realClass` to get the actual implementation class when needed\n\nThis fix ensures that CDI proxy beans in Quarkus can be properly identified by their annotations, resolving the issue where proxy classes were hiding the actual class annotations."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"4592f773-f640-4940-8cd1-16bfd1d37cec"}
