{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KKiaZa5ttZMP8rm3Q4PU9E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n    21→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirectDBUtils;\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    25→\n    26→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    31→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    32→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    33→\n    34→/**\n    35→ * TradeConfigServlet provides a servlet interface to adjust DayTrader runtime\n    36→ * parameters.\n    37→ * TradeConfigServlet updates values in the\n    38→ * {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.TradeConfig} JavaBean holding\n    39→ * all configuration and runtime parameters for the Trade application\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→@WebServlet(name = \"TradeConfigServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/config\" })\n    43→@Trace\n    44→public class TradeConfigServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    45→\n    46→    @Inject\n    47→    private TradeDirectDBUtils dbUtils;\n    48→\n    49→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -1910381529792500095L;\n    50→\n    51→    /**\n    52→     * Servlet initialization method.\n    53→     */\n    54→    @Override\n    55→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    56→        super.init(config);\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    /**\n    60→     * Create the TradeConfig bean and pass it the config.jsp page\n    61→     * to display the current Trade runtime configuration\n    62→     * Creation date: (2/8/2000 3:43:59 PM)\n    63→     */\n    64→    void doConfigDisplay(\n    65→            HttpServletRequest req,\n    66→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n    67→            String results) throws Exception {\n    68→        TradeConfig currentConfig = new TradeConfig();\n    69→\n    70→        req.setAttribute(\"tradeConfig\", currentConfig);\n    71→        req.setAttribute(\"status\", results);\n    72→        getServletConfig()\n    73→                .getServletContext()\n    74→                .getRequestDispatcher(TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.CONFIG_PAGE))\n    75→                .include(req, resp);\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    void doResetTrade(\n    79→            HttpServletRequest req,\n    80→            HttpServletResponse resp,\n    81→            String results) throws Exception {\n    82→        RunStatsDataBean runStatsData = new RunStatsDataBean();\n    83→        TradeConfig currentConfig = new TradeConfig();\n    84→\n    85→        try {\n    86→            runStatsData = dbUtils.resetTrade(false);\n    87→\n    88→            req.setAttribute(\"runStatsData\", runStatsData);\n    89→            req.setAttribute(\"tradeConfig\", currentConfig);\n    90→            results += \"Trade Reset completed successfully\";\n    91→            req.setAttribute(\"status\", results);\n    92→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    93→            results += \"Trade Reset Error  - see log for details\";\n    94→            Log.error(e, results);\n    95→            throw e;\n    96→        }\n    97→        getServletConfig()\n    98→                .getServletContext()\n    99→                .getRequestDispatcher(TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.STATS_PAGE))\n   100→                .include(req, resp);\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    /**\n   104→     * Update Trade runtime configuration paramaters\n   105→     * Creation date: (2/8/2000 3:44:24 PM)\n   106→     */\n   107→    void doConfigUpdate(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp)\n   108→            throws Exception {\n   109→        String currentConfigStr = \"\\n\\n########## Trade configuration update. Current config:\\n\\n\";\n   110→\n   111→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tRuntimeMode:\\t\\t\" +\n   112→                TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] +\n   113→                \"\\n\";\n   114→\n   115→        String orderProcessingModeStr = req.getParameter(\"OrderProcessingMode\");\n   116→        if (orderProcessingModeStr != null) {\n   117→            try {\n   118→                int i = Integer.parseInt(orderProcessingModeStr);\n   119→                if ((i >= 0) &&\n   120→                        (i < TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames().length) // Input validation\n   121→                )\n   122→                    TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(i);\n   123→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   124→                // >>rjm\n   125→                Log.error(\n   126→                        e,\n   127→                        \"TradeConfigServlet.doConfigUpdate(..): minor exception caught\",\n   128→                        \"trying to set orderProcessing to \" +\n   129→                                orderProcessingModeStr,\n   130→                        \"reverting to current value\");\n   131→            } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   132→        }\n   133→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tOrderProcessingMode:\\t\\t\" +\n   134→                TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()] +\n   135→                \"\\n\";\n   136→\n   137→        String webInterfaceStr = req.getParameter(\"WebInterface\");\n   138→        if (webInterfaceStr != null) {\n   139→            try {\n   140→                int i = Integer.parseInt(webInterfaceStr);\n   141→                if ((i >= 0) && (i < TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames().length) // Input validation\n   142→                )\n   143→                    TradeConfig.setWebInterface(i);\n   144→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   145→                Log.error(\n   146→                        e,\n   147→                        \"TradeConfigServlet.doConfigUpdate(..): minor exception caught\",\n   148→                        \"trying to set WebInterface to \" + webInterfaceStr,\n   149→                        \"reverting to current value\");\n   150→            } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   151→        }\n   152→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tWeb Interface:\\t\\t\\t\" +\n   153→                TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames()[TradeConfig.getWebInterface()] +\n   154→                \"\\n\";\n   155→\n   156→        String parm = req.getParameter(\"MaxUsers\");\n   157→        if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   158→            try {\n   159→                TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   160→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   161→                Log.error(\n   162→                        e,\n   163→                        \"TradeConfigServlet.doConfigUpdate(..): minor exception caught\",\n   164→                        \"Setting maxusers, probably error parsing string to int:\" +\n   165→                                parm,\n   166→                        \"revertying to current value: \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS());\n   167→            } // On error, revert to saved\n   168→        }\n   169→        parm = req.getParameter(\"MaxQuotes\");\n   170→        if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   171→            try {\n   172→                TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   173→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   174→                // >>rjm\n   175→                Log.error(\n   176→                        e,\n   177→                        \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\",\n   178→                        \"trying to set max_quotes, error on parsing int \" + parm,\n   179→                        \"reverting to current value \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES());\n   180→                // <<rjm\n   181→            } // On error, revert to saved\n   182→        }\n   183→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTrade Users:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \"\\n\";\n   184→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTrade Quotes:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() + \"\\n\";\n   185→\n   186→        parm = req.getParameter(\"marketSummaryInterval\");\n   187→        if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   188→            try {\n   189→                TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   190→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   191→                Log.error(\n   192→                        e,\n   193→                        \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\",\n   194→                        \"trying to set marketSummaryInterval, error on parsing int \" +\n   195→                                parm,\n   196→                        \"reverting to current value \" +\n   197→                                TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval());\n   198→            }\n   199→        }\n   200→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tMarket Summary Interval:\\t\" +\n   201→                TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() +\n   202→                \"\\n\";\n   203→\n   204→        parm = req.getParameter(\"primIterations\");\n   205→        if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   206→            try {\n   207→                TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   208→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   209→                Log.error(\n   210→                        e,\n   211→                        \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\",\n   212→                        \"trying to set primIterations, error on parsing int \" +\n   213→                                parm,\n   214→                        \"reverting to current value \" +\n   215→                                TradeConfig.getPrimIterations());\n   216→            }\n   217→        }\n   218→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tPrimitive Iterations:\\t\\t\" +\n   219→                TradeConfig.getPrimIterations() +\n   220→                \"\\n\";\n   221→\n   222→        String enablePublishQuotePriceChange = req.getParameter(\n   223→                \"EnablePublishQuotePriceChange\");\n   224→\n   225→        if (enablePublishQuotePriceChange != null)\n   226→            TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(true);\n   227→        else\n   228→            TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(false);\n   229→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTradeStreamer MDB Enabled:\\t\" +\n   230→                TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange() +\n   231→                \"\\n\";\n   232→\n   233→        parm = req.getParameter(\"ListQuotePriceChangeFrequency\");\n   234→        if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   235→            try {\n   236→                TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(\n   237→                        Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   238→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   239→                Log.error(\n   240→                        e,\n   241→                        \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\",\n   242→                        \"trying to set percentSentToWebSocket, error on parsing int \" +\n   243→                                parm,\n   244→                        \"reverting to current value \" +\n   245→                                TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency());\n   246→            }\n   247→        }\n   248→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\t% of trades on Websocket:\\t\" +\n   249→                TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() +\n   250→                \"\\n\";\n   251→\n   252→        String enableLongRun = req.getParameter(\"EnableLongRun\");\n   253→\n   254→        if (enableLongRun != null)\n   255→            TradeConfig.setLongRun(true);\n   256→        else\n   257→            TradeConfig.setLongRun(false);\n   258→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tLong Run Enabled:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getLongRun() + \"\\n\";\n   259→\n   260→        String displayOrderAlerts = req.getParameter(\"DisplayOrderAlerts\");\n   261→\n   262→        if (displayOrderAlerts != null)\n   263→            TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(true);\n   264→        else\n   265→            TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(false);\n   266→        currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tDisplay Order Alerts:\\t\\t\" +\n   267→                TradeConfig.getDisplayOrderAlerts() +\n   268→                \"\\n\";\n   269→\n   270→        System.out.println(currentConfigStr);\n   271→    }\n   272→\n   273→    @Override\n   274→    public void service(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp)\n   275→            throws ServletException, IOException {\n   276→        String action = null;\n   277→        String result = \"\";\n   278→\n   279→        resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   280→        try {\n   281→            action = req.getParameter(\"action\");\n   282→            if (action == null) {\n   283→                doConfigDisplay(\n   284→                        req,\n   285→                        resp,\n   286→                        result + \"<b><br>Current DayTrader Configuration:</br></b>\");\n   287→                return;\n   288→            } else if (action.equals(\"updateConfig\")) {\n   289→                doConfigUpdate(req, resp);\n   290→                result = \"<B><BR>DayTrader Configuration Updated</BR></B>\";\n   291→            } else if (action.equals(\"resetTrade\")) {\n   292→                doResetTrade(req, resp, \"\");\n   293→                return;\n   294→            } else if (action.equals(\"buildDB\")) {\n   295→                resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   296→                dbUtils.buildDB(resp.getWriter(), null);\n   297→                result = \"DayTrader Database Built - \" +\n   298→                        TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() +\n   299→                        \"users created\";\n   300→            } else if (action.equals(\"buildDBTables\")) {\n   301→                resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   302→\n   303→                String dbProductName = null;\n   304→                try {\n   305→                    dbProductName = dbUtils.checkDBProductName();\n   306→                } catch (Exception e) {\n   307→                    Log.error(\n   308→                            e,\n   309→                            \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to check DB Product name\");\n   310→                }\n   311→                if (dbProductName == null) {\n   312→                    resp\n   313→                            .getWriter()\n   314→                            .println(\n   315→                                    \"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to check DB Product name, please check Database/AppServer configuration and retry ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   316→                    return;\n   317→                }\n   318→\n   319→                String ddlFile = null;\n   320→                // Locate DDL file for the specified database\n   321→                try {\n   322→                    resp\n   323→                            .getWriter()\n   324→                            .println(\n   325→                                    \"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Database Product detected: \" +\n   326→                                            dbProductName +\n   327→                                            \" ****</BR>\");\n   328→                    if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"DB2/\")) {\n   329→                        // if db is DB2\n   330→                        ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/db2/Table.ddl\";\n   331→                    } else if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"Apache Derby\")) {\n   332→                        // if db is Derby\n   333→                        ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/derby/Table.ddl\";\n   334→                    } else if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"Oracle\")) {\n   335→                        // if the Db is Oracle\n   336→                        ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/oracle/Table.ddl\";\n   337→                    } else {\n   338→                        // Unsupported \"Other\" Database\n   339→                        ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/other/Table.ddl\";\n   340→                        resp\n   341→                                .getWriter()\n   342→                                .println(\n   343→                                        \"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** This Database is unsupported/untested use at your own risk ****</BR>\");\n   344→                    }\n   345→\n   346→                    resp\n   347→                            .getWriter()\n   348→                            .println(\n   349→                                    \"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** The DDL file at path <I>\" +\n   350→                                            ddlFile +\n   351→                                            \"</I> will be used ****</BR>\");\n   352→                    resp.getWriter().flush();\n   353→                } catch (Exception e) {\n   354→                    Log.error(\n   355→                            e,\n   356→                            \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to locate DDL file for the specified database\");\n   357→                    resp\n   358→                            .getWriter()\n   359→                            .println(\n   360→                                    \"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to locate DDL file for the specified database ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   361→                    return;\n   362→                }\n   363→\n   364→                dbUtils.buildDB(\n   365→                        resp.getWriter(),\n   366→                        getServletContext().getResourceAsStream(ddlFile));\n   367→            }\n   368→            doConfigDisplay(\n   369→                    req,\n   370→                    resp,\n   371→                    result + \"Current DayTrader Configuration:\");\n   372→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   373→            Log.error(\n   374→                    e,\n   375→                    \"TradeConfigServlet.service(...)\",\n   376→                    \"Exception trying to perform action=\" + action);\n   377→\n   378→            resp.sendError(\n   379→                    500,\n   380→                    \"TradeConfigServlet.service(...)\" +\n   381→                            \"Exception trying to perform action=\" +\n   382→                            action +\n   383→                            \"\\nException details: \" +\n   384→                            e.toString());\n   385→        }\n   386→    }\n   387→}\n   388→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"9cbf59bb-5f61-43ff-abe7-4d8a3b003cfd"}
