{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UjkVU83e5MLXo8mWg4z74v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→import java.util.Iterator;\n    22→\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    26→\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.ServletContext;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    30→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    31→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    32→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    33→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    34→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * TradeScenarioServlet emulates a population of web users by generating a\n    38→ * specific Trade operation for a randomly chosen user on each access to the\n    39→ * URL. Test this servlet by clicking Trade Scenario and hit \"Reload\" on your\n    40→ * browser to step through a Trade Scenario. To benchmark using this URL aim\n    41→ * your favorite web load generator (such as AKStress) at the Trade Scenario URL\n    42→ * and fire away.\n    43→ */\n    44→@WebServlet(name = \"TradeScenarioServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/scenario\" })\n    45→public class TradeScenarioServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    46→\n    47→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1410005249314201829L;\n    48→\n    49→    /**\n    50→     * Servlet initialization method.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"8379e43d-b303-4870-934b-3cb9db669352"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01JXUWxkLArRX48q8uuaQo5Q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01YRTnrBbMRj6dG4Xg7YNA7q","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeScenarioServlet.java","offset":50,"limit":100}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1221,"cache_read_input_tokens":125289,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1221,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":167},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c480d6c7-effa-4713-82f1-393630b82f02"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YRTnrBbMRj6dG4Xg7YNA7q","type":"tool_result","content":"    50→     * Servlet initialization method.\n    51→     */\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    54→        super.init(config);\n    55→        java.util.Enumeration<String> en = config.getInitParameterNames();\n    56→        while (en.hasMoreElements()) {\n    57→            String parm = en.nextElement();\n    58→            String value = config.getInitParameter(parm);\n    59→            TradeConfig.setConfigParam(parm, value);\n    60→        }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    /**\n    64→     * Returns a string that contains information about TradeScenarioServlet\n    65→     *\n    66→     * @return The servlet information\n    67→     */\n    68→    @Override\n    69→    public java.lang.String getServletInfo() {\n    70→        return \"TradeScenarioServlet emulates a population of web users\";\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Process incoming HTTP GET requests\n    75→     *\n    76→     * @param request\n    77→     *                 Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    78→     * @param response\n    79→     *                 Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    80→     */\n    81→    @Override\n    82→    public void doGet(\n    83→            jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,\n    84→            jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    85→        performTask(request, response);\n    86→    }\n    87→\n    88→    /**\n    89→     * Process incoming HTTP POST requests\n    90→     *\n    91→     * @param request\n    92→     *                 Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    93→     * @param response\n    94→     *                 Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    95→     */\n    96→    @Override\n    97→    public void doPost(\n    98→            jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,\n    99→            jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   100→        performTask(request, response);\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    /**\n   104→     * Main service method for TradeScenarioServlet\n   105→     *\n   106→     * @param request\n   107→     *                 Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n   108→     * @param response\n   109→     *                 Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n   110→     */\n   111→    public void performTask(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp)\n   112→            throws ServletException, IOException {\n   113→        // Scenario generator for Trade2\n   114→        char action = ' ';\n   115→        String userID = null;\n   116→\n   117→        // String to create full dispatch path to TradeAppServlet w/ request\n   118→        // Parameters\n   119→        String dispPath = null; // Dispatch Path to TradeAppServlet\n   120→\n   121→        resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   122→\n   123→        String scenarioAction = req.getParameter(\"action\");\n   124→        if ((scenarioAction != null) && (scenarioAction.length() >= 1)) {\n   125→            action = scenarioAction.charAt(0);\n   126→            if (action == 'n') {\n   127→                // null;\n   128→                try {\n   129→                    // resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   130→                    PrintWriter out = new PrintWriter(resp.getOutputStream());\n   131→                    out.println(\n   132→                            \"<HTML><HEAD>TradeScenarioServlet</HEAD><BODY>Hello</BODY></HTML>\");\n   133→                    out.close();\n   134→                    return;\n   135→                } catch (Exception e) {\n   136→                    Log.error(\n   137→                            \"trade_client.TradeScenarioServlet.service(...)\" +\n   138→                                    \"error creating printwriter from responce.getOutputStream\",\n   139→                            e);\n   140→\n   141→                    resp.sendError(\n   142→                            500,\n   143→                            \"trade_client.TradeScenarioServlet.service(...): erorr creating and writing to PrintStream created from response.getOutputStream()\");\n   144→                } // end of catch\n   145→            } // end of action=='n'\n   146→        }\n   147→\n   148→        ServletContext ctx = null;\n   149→        HttpSession session = null;\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"a0c3e819-8cdb-4301-b3b2-72d38d739bff"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0158FsZ4m4PLqEMSPbcU5v74","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012S8ChqwRDUCkN98AU7yw8p","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__spring__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeScenarioServlet.java","offset":150,"limit":200}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1446,"cache_read_input_tokens":126510,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1446,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":167},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"14188dbc-9183-46a1-9fd7-f31c904d48a0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012S8ChqwRDUCkN98AU7yw8p","type":"tool_result","content":"   150→        try {\n   151→            ctx = getServletConfig().getServletContext();\n   152→            // These operations require the user to be logged in. Verify the\n   153→            // user and if not logged in\n   154→            // change the operation to a login\n   155→            session = req.getSession(true);\n   156→            userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n   157→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   158→            Log.error(\n   159→                    \"trade_client.TradeScenarioServlet.service(...): performing \" +\n   160→                            scenarioAction +\n   161→                            \"error getting ServletContext,HttpSession, or UserID from session\" +\n   162→                            \"will make scenarioAction a login and try to recover from there\",\n   163→                    e);\n   164→            userID = null;\n   165→            action = 'l';\n   166→        }\n   167→\n   168→        if (userID == null) {\n   169→            action = 'l'; // change to login\n   170→            TradeConfig.incrementScenarioCount();\n   171→        } else if (action == ' ') {\n   172→            // action is not specified perform a random operation according to\n   173→            // current mix\n   174→            // Tell getScenarioAction if we are an original user or a registered\n   175→            // user\n   176→            // -- sellDeficits should only be compensated for with original\n   177→            // users.\n   178→            action = TradeConfig.getScenarioAction(\n   179→                    userID.startsWith(TradeConfig.newUserPrefix));\n   180→        }\n   181→        switch (action) {\n   182→            case 'q': // quote\n   183→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix +\n   184→                        \"quotes&symbols=\" +\n   185→                        TradeConfig.rndSymbols();\n   186→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   187→                break;\n   188→            case 'a': // account\n   189→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"account\";\n   190→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   191→                break;\n   192→            case 'u': // update account profile\n   193→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"account\";\n   194→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   195→\n   196→                String fullName = \"rnd\" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n   197→                String address = \"rndAddress\";\n   198→                String password = \"xxx\";\n   199→                String email = \"rndEmail\";\n   200→                String creditcard = \"rndCC\";\n   201→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix +\n   202→                        \"update_profile&fullname=\" +\n   203→                        fullName +\n   204→                        \"&password=\" +\n   205→                        password +\n   206→                        \"&cpassword=\" +\n   207→                        password +\n   208→                        \"&address=\" +\n   209→                        address +\n   210→                        \"&email=\" +\n   211→                        email +\n   212→                        \"&creditcard=\" +\n   213→                        creditcard;\n   214→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   215→                break;\n   216→            case 'h': // home\n   217→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"home\";\n   218→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   219→                break;\n   220→            case 'l': // login\n   221→                userID = TradeConfig.getUserID();\n   222→                String password2 = \"xxx\";\n   223→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix +\n   224→                        \"login&inScenario=true&uid=\" +\n   225→                        userID +\n   226→                        \"&passwd=\" +\n   227→                        password2;\n   228→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   229→\n   230→                // login is successful if the userID is written to the HTTP session\n   231→                if (session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\") == null) {\n   232→                    System.out.println(\n   233→                            \"TradeScenario login failed. Reset DB between runs\");\n   234→                }\n   235→                break;\n   236→            case 'o': // logout\n   237→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"logout\";\n   238→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   239→                break;\n   240→            case 'p': // portfolio\n   241→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"portfolio\";\n   242→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   243→                break;\n   244→            case 'r': // register\n   245→                // Logout the current user to become a new user\n   246→                // see note in TradeServletAction\n   247→                req.setAttribute(\"TSS-RecreateSessionInLogout\", Boolean.TRUE);\n   248→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"logout\";\n   249→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   250→\n   251→                userID = TradeConfig.rndNewUserID();\n   252→                String passwd = \"yyy\";\n   253→                fullName = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   254→                creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   255→                String money = TradeConfig.rndBalance();\n   256→                email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   257→                String smail = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   258→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix +\n   259→                        \"register&Full Name=\" +\n   260→                        fullName +\n   261→                        \"&snail mail=\" +\n   262→                        smail +\n   263→                        \"&email=\" +\n   264→                        email +\n   265→                        \"&user id=\" +\n   266→                        userID +\n   267→                        \"&passwd=\" +\n   268→                        passwd +\n   269→                        \"&confirm passwd=\" +\n   270→                        passwd +\n   271→                        \"&money=\" +\n   272→                        money +\n   273→                        \"&Credit Card Number=\" +\n   274→                        creditcard;\n   275→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   276→                break;\n   277→            case 's': // sell\n   278→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"portfolioNoEdge\";\n   279→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   280→\n   281→                Collection<?> holdings = (Collection<?>) req.getAttribute(\n   282→                        \"holdingDataBeans\");\n   283→                int numHoldings = holdings.size();\n   284→                if (numHoldings > 0) {\n   285→                    // sell first available security out of holding\n   286→\n   287→                    Iterator<?> it = holdings.iterator();\n   288→                    boolean foundHoldingToSell = false;\n   289→                    while (it.hasNext()) {\n   290→                        HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) it.next();\n   291→                        if (!(holdingData\n   292→                                .getPurchaseDate()\n   293→                                .equals(new java.util.Date(0)))) {\n   294→                            Integer holdingID = holdingData.getHoldingID();\n   295→\n   296→                            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"sell&holdingID=\" + holdingID;\n   297→                            ctx\n   298→                                    .getRequestDispatcher(dispPath)\n   299→                                    .include(req, resp);\n   300→                            foundHoldingToSell = true;\n   301→                            break;\n   302→                        }\n   303→                    }\n   304→                    if (foundHoldingToSell) {\n   305→                        break;\n   306→                    }\n   307→\n   308→                    Log.trace(\n   309→                            \"TradeScenario: No holding to sell -switch to buy -- userID = \" +\n   310→                                    userID +\n   311→                                    \"  Collection count = \" +\n   312→                                    numHoldings);\n   313→                }\n   314→                // At this point: A TradeScenario Sell was requested with No Stocks\n   315→                // in Portfolio\n   316→                // This can happen when a new registered user happens to request a\n   317→                // sell before a buy\n   318→                // In this case, fall through and perform a buy instead\n   319→\n   320→                /*\n   321→                 * Trade 2.037: Added sell_deficit counter to maintain correct\n   322→                 * buy/sell mix. When a users portfolio is reduced to 0 holdings, a\n   323→                 * buy is requested instead of a sell. This throws off the buy/sell\n   324→                 * mix by 1. This results in unwanted holding table growth To fix\n   325→                 * this we increment a sell deficit counter to maintain the correct\n   326→                 * ratio in getScenarioAction The 'z' action from getScenario\n   327→                 * denotes that this is a sell action that was switched from a buy\n   328→                 * to reduce a sellDeficit\n   329→                 */\n   330→                if (userID.startsWith(TradeConfig.newUserPrefix) == false) {\n   331→                    TradeConfig.incrementSellDeficit();\n   332→                }\n   333→            case 'b': // buy\n   334→                String symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n   335→                String amount = TradeConfig.rndQuantity() + \"\";\n   336→\n   337→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"quotes&symbols=\" + symbol;\n   338→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   339→\n   340→                dispPath = tasPathPrefix +\n   341→                        \"buy&quantity=\" +\n   342→                        amount +\n   343→                        \"&symbol=\" +\n   344→                        symbol;\n   345→                ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   346→                break;\n   347→        } // end of switch statement\n   348→    }\n   349→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"fad1b6e3-13a9-46e4-824b-8c64e96f7140"}
