{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NJzSP6m75WCt3HPs2uXkgb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The users are `uid:8925` and `uid:2409` - those userIDs seem too high. The default MAX_USERS is 500, so users would be `uid:0` to `uid:499`. But `TradeConfig.getUserID()` generates random user IDs. Let me check what userIDs were created with buildDB. The issue is that the user IDs in TradeConfig use format \"uid:X\" where X goes from 0 to MAX_USERS-1, but the DB build probably used a different MAX_USERS setting.\n\nLet me check the runtime config and try to understand the user ID range issue:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":244,"cache_read_input_tokens":140494,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":244,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":249},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"f9269ce1-bd05-4d1c-a6ad-9a10c3c89278"}
