{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_017Svh8B9eDQUgvGHudNWzaA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait - the `updateConfig` action also calls `doConfigDisplay` which depends on the config page. But I also need to check if the `RuntimeMode` parameter is being processed. Looking at `doConfigUpdate`, it doesn't process `RuntimeMode` — it processes `OrderProcessingMode`, `WebInterface`, `MaxUsers`, `MaxQuotes`, etc. But `RuntimeMode` is only set at startup.\n\nThe real fix should be to change the default `daytrader.runtime-mode` to use `0` (Direct JDBC) instead of `1` (Full EJB3), or to properly initialize the datasource in the TradeDirect path.\n\nActually, the simpler approach is to change the default runtime mode to `0` (Direct JDBC) in the application.properties:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":98107,"cache_read_input_tokens":14809,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":98107,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":372},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"ca9d6bb8-bc5c-46a3-a6b6-636dafd8408f"}
