{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BLDXTuaosyeaCZGfG8JBsh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Same issue. The problem is the runtime mode. Even though I set it to 0 in config, the `OrdersAlertFilter` was initialized at startup with mode 1 (Full EJB3), and the scenario servlet also depends on the runtime mode that was set at startup.\n\nLet me examine the problem more carefully. The `TradeScenarioServlet` dispatches to `TradeAppServlet` which uses `TradeServletAction`. The `TradeServletAction` resolves the trade service. Let me check the TradeServletAction.getTradeAction() method:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":127,"cache_read_input_tokens":115787,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":127,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":297},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"c582e0c9-37b1-4cb1-8e27-ee752123e21a"}
