{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KMo4VnbBc2cFpnNyXGZEgU","type":"tool_result","content":"    56→\n    57→        private TradeServices tAction;\n    58→\n    59→        @Inject\n    60→        @jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any\n    61→        jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance<com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices> tradeServicesInstance;\n    62→\n    63→        public TradeServletAction() {\n    64→        }\n    65→\n    66→        @PostConstruct\n    67→        void resolveTradeServices() {\n    68→                String key = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()];\n    69→                // Iterate through available TradeServices implementations to find the matching one\n    70→                for (TradeServices ts : tradeServicesInstance) {\n    71→                        // Check the bean name/qualifier\n    72→                        String beanName = getBeanName(ts);\n    73→                        if (key.equals(beanName)) {\n    74→                                this.tAction = ts;\n    75→                                break;\n    76→                        }\n    77→                }\n    78→                if (this.tAction == null) {\n    79→                        java.util.List<String> available = new ArrayList<>();\n    80→                        for (TradeServices ts : tradeServicesInstance) {\n    81→                                available.add(getBeanName(ts));\n    82→                        }\n    83→                        throw new IllegalStateException(\"No TradeServices bean named '\" + key + \"' (available: \" + available + \")\");\n    84→                }\n    85→        }\n    86→\n    87→        private String getBeanName(TradeServices ts) {\n    88→                // CDI proxy classes need getSuperclass() to find the actual class with annotations\n    89→                Class<?> clazz = ts.getClass();\n    90→                jakarta.inject.Named named = clazz.getAnnotation(jakarta.inject.Named.class);\n    91→                if (named == null && clazz.getSuperclass() != null) {\n    92→                        named = clazz.getSuperclass().getAnnotation(jakarta.inject.Named.class);\n    93→                }\n    94→                if (named != null && !named.value().isEmpty()) {\n    95→                        return named.value();\n    96→                }\n    97→                // Check superclass for qualifier annotations too\n    98→                Class<?> realClass = clazz;\n    99→                if (realClass.getSuperclass() != null && realClass.getSuperclass() != Object.class) {\n   100→                        realClass = realClass.getSuperclass();\n   101→                }\n   102→                if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC.class) != null) {\n   103→                        return \"Direct (JDBC)\";\n   104→                }\n   105→                if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB.class) != null) {\n   106→                        return \"Full EJB3\";\n   107→                }\n   108→                if (realClass.getAnnotation(com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeSession2Direct.class) != null) {\n   109→                        return \"Session to Direct\";\n   110→                }\n   111→                // Default to simple class name\n   112→                String simpleName = realClass.getSimpleName();\n   113→                return simpleName;\n   114→        }\n   115→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4e