{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WWWnyiv4exFhVEEGpXLvdD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `doConfigUpdate` method does NOT process `RuntimeMode` (it just logs the current runtime mode but never sets it). This is because the runtime mode was meant to be set only at startup. So I need a different approach - either:\n\n1. Add RuntimeMode processing to doConfigUpdate, or\n2. Set the default runtime mode in application.properties, or\n3. Change the approach entirely\n\nSince the application.properties already sets `daytrader.runtime-mode=1` (Direct JDBC), the issue is that the `TradeConfig` static initializer doesn't read from application.properties in Quarkus. Let me check how `TradeConfig` initializes the runtime mode:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":448,"cache_read_input_tokens":134180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":448,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":312},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"022e9816-6741-40b8-b86f-2dc3ea31dddb"}
