{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KC32jymj1gdHeSzD2qbFjB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import java.io.InputStream;\n     8→import java.util.Properties;\n     9→\n    10→/**\n    11→ * Quarkus startup initializer for DayTrader config.\n    12→ * In-place replacement for the old ServletContextListener+JSF class.\n    13→ */\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→public class TradeWebContextListener {\n    16→\n    17→    public TradeWebContextListener() {\n    18→    }\n    19→\n    20→    /** Helper: try ENV first, then MicroProfile Config, then legacy properties file */\n    21→    private String s(Properties prop, String... keys) {\n    22→        // Try system properties and environment variables first\n    23→        for (String k : keys) {\n    24→            String v = System.getProperty(k);\n    25→            if (v != null) return v;\n    26→            v = System.getenv(k);\n    27→            if (v != null) return v;\n    28→        }\n    29→        // Try MicroProfile Config\n    30→        try {\n    31→            org.eclipse.microprofile.config.Config config = org.eclipse.microprofile.config.ConfigProvider.getConfig();\n    32→            for (String k : keys) {\n    33→                java.util.Optional<String> v = config.getOptionalValue(k, String.class);\n    34→                if (v.isPresent()) return v.get();\n    35→            }\n    36→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    37→            // Config not available, continue\n    38→        }\n    39→        // Fall back to properties file\n    40→        for (String k : keys) {\n    41→            String v = prop.getProperty(k);\n    42→            if (v != null) return v;\n    43→        }\n    44→        return null;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @PostConstruct\n    48→    public void init() {\n    49→        Log.trace(\"TradeWebContextListener initializing (Quarkus)\");\n    50→\n    51→        // Optional legacy file: classpath:properties/daytrader.properties\n    52→        Properties prop = new Properties();\n    53→        try {\n    54→            InputStream in = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()\n    55→                .getResourceAsStream(\"properties/daytrader.properties\");\n    56→            if (in != null) {\n    57→                try (InputStream stream = in) {\n    58→                    prop.load(stream);\n    59→                    System.out.println(\n    60→                        \"Settings from daytrader.properties: \" + prop\n    61→                    );\n    62→                }\n    63→            } else {\n    64→                System.out.println(\n    65→                    \"daytrader.properties not found (classpath)\"\n    66→                );\n    67→            }\n    68→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    69→            System.out.println(\"Failed to load daytrader.properties (ignored)\");\n    70→        }\n    71→\n    72→        try {\n    73→            // Mirrors your original precedence but adds daytrader.* YAML keys in between.\n    74→            String rt = s(\n    75→                prop,\n    76→                \"RUNTIME_MODE\",\n    77→                \"daytrader.runtime-mode\",\n    78→                \"runtimeMode\"\n    79→            );\n    80→            if (rt != null) TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode(Integer.parseInt(rt));\n    81→\n    82→            String op = s(\n    83→                prop,\n    84→                \"ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE\",\n    85→                \"daytrader.order-processing-mode\",\n    86→                \"orderProcessingMode\"\n    87→            );\n    88→            if (op != null) TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(\n    89→                Integer.parseInt(op)\n    90→            );\n    91→\n    92→            String mu = s(prop, \"MAX_USERS\", \"daytrader.max-users\", \"maxUsers\");\n    93→            if (mu != null) TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(mu));\n    94→\n    95→            String mq = s(\n    96→                prop,\n    97→                \"MAX_QUOTES\",\n    98→                \"daytrader.max-quotes\",\n    99→                \"maxQuotes\"\n   100→            );\n   101→            if (mq != null) TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(mq));\n   102→\n   103→            String pub = s(\n   104→                prop,\n   105→                \"PUBLISH_QUOTES\",\n   106→                \"daytrader.publish-quotes\",\n   107→                \"publishQuotePriceChange\"\n   108→            );\n   109→            if (pub != null) TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(\n   110→                Boolean.parseBoolean(pub)\n   111→            );\n   112→\n   113→            String alerts = s(\n   114→                prop,\n   115→                \"DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS\",\n   116→                \"daytrader.display-order-alerts\",\n   117→                \"displayOrderAlerts\"\n   118→            );\n   119→            if (alerts != null) TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(\n   120→                Boolean.parseBoolean(alerts)\n   121→            );\n   122→\n   123→            String wi = s(\n   124→                prop,\n   125→                \"WEB_INTERFACE\",\n   126→                \"daytrader.web-interface\",\n   127→                \"webInterface\"\n   128→            );\n   129→            if (wi != null) TradeConfig.setWebInterface(Integer.parseInt(wi));\n   130→\n   131→            String freq = s(\n   132→                prop,\n   133→                \"LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\",\n   134→                \"daytrader.list-quote-price-change-frequency\",\n   135→                \"listQuotePriceChangeFrequency\"\n   136→            );\n   137→            if (freq != null) TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(\n   138→                Integer.parseInt(freq)\n   139→            );\n   140→\n   141→            // File-only in your original code — we also allow YAML keys\n   142→            String prim = s(\n   143→                prop,\n   144→                \"daytrader.prim-iterations\",\n   145→                \"primIterations\"\n   146→            );\n   147→            if (prim != null) TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(\n   148→                Integer.parseInt(prim)\n   149→            );\n   150→\n   151→            String msi = s(\n   152→                prop,\n   153→                \"daytrader.market-summary-interval\",\n   154→                \"marketSummaryInterval\"\n   155→            );\n   156→            if (msi != null) TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(\n   157→                Integer.parseInt(msi)\n   158→            );\n   159→\n   160→            String lr = s(prop, \"daytrader.long-run\", \"longRun\");\n   161→            if (lr != null) TradeConfig.setLongRun(Boolean.parseBoolean(lr));\n   162→\n   163→            System.out.print(\n   164→                \"Running in \" +\n   165→                TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] +\n   166→                \" Mode\"\n   167→            );\n   168→            System.out.print(\n   169→                \" | Order Processing \" +\n   170→                TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()]\n   171→            );\n   172→            System.out.print(\" | MAX_USERS=\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS());\n   173→            System.out.print(\" | MAX_QUOTES=\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES());\n   174→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   175→            Log.error(\"Error initializing TradeConfig\", e);\n   176→        }\n   177→    }\n   178→}\n   179→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"ceac473c-f7ee-4d68-a03c-6e499eaa9567"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01X3uoZZP5uk1NHL4H3Roa5D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `TradeWebContextListener` correctly reads `daytrader.runtime-mode` from MicroProfile Config and sets `TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode()`. But the issue might be that this `@ApplicationScoped @PostConstruct` bean is not being eagerly initialized. In Quarkus, `@ApplicationScoped` beans are lazy by default. \n\nThe solution is to make it eager. I need to add `@io.quarkus.runtime.Startup` annotation:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2508,"cache_read_input_tokens":135966,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2508,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":315},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56efa089-e1a8-4ed6-8ae5-0ef3f5d72aa6","uuid":"861ecef8-98b8-4d96-ac88-91b3b7405ebe"}
